103// Line type
104// RFC 4566
105// An SDP session description consists of a number of lines of text of
106// the form:
107// <type>=<value>
108// where <type> MUST be exactly one case-significant character.
109
110// Legal characters in a <token> value (RFC 4566 section 9):
111// token-char = %x21 / %x23-27 / %x2A-2B / %x2D-2E / %x30-39
112// / %x41-5A / %x5E-7E
113static const char kLegalTokenCharacters[] =
114 "!#$%&'*+-." // %x21, %x23-27, %x2A-2B, %x2D-2E
115 "0123456789" // %x30-39
116 "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ" // %x41-5A
117 "^_`abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz{|}~"; // %x5E-7E
118static const int kLinePrefixLength = 2; // Length of <type>=
119static const char kLineTypeVersion = 'v';
120static const char kLineTypeOrigin = 'o';
121static const char kLineTypeSessionName = 's';
122static const char kLineTypeSessionInfo = 'i';
123static const char kLineTypeSessionUri = 'u';
124static const char kLineTypeSessionEmail = 'e';
125static const char kLineTypeSessionPhone = 'p';
126static const char kLineTypeSessionBandwidth = 'b';
127static const char kLineTypeTiming = 't';
128static const char kLineTypeRepeatTimes = 'r';
129static const char kLineTypeTimeZone = 'z';
130static const char kLineTypeEncryptionKey = 'k';
131static const char kLineTypeMedia = 'm';
132static const char kLineTypeConnection = 'c';
133static const char kLineTypeAttributes = 'a';

388// Helper functions
389
390// Below ParseFailed*** functions output the line that caused the parsing
391// failure and the detailed reason (|description|) of the failure to |error|.
392// The functions always return false so that they can be used directly in the
393// following way when error happens:
394// "return ParseFailed***(...);"
395
396// The line starting at |line_start| of |message| is the failing line.
397// The reason for the failure should be provided in the |description|.
398// An example of a description could be "unknown character".
399static bool ParseFailed(const std::string& message,
400 size_t line_start,
401 const std::string& description,
402 SdpParseError* error) {
403 // Get the first line of |message| from |line_start|.
404 std::string first_line;
405 size_t line_end = message.find(kNewLine, line_start);
406 if (line_end != std::string::npos) {
407 if (line_end > 0 && (message.at(line_end - 1) == kReturnChar)) {
408 --line_end;
409 }
410 first_line = message.substr(line_start, (line_end - line_start));
411 } else {
412 first_line = message.substr(line_start);
413 }
414
415 if (error) {
416 error->line = first_line;
417 error->description = description;
418 }
419 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to parse: \"" << first_line
420 << "\". Reason: " << description;
421 return false;
422}
423
424// |line| is the failing line. The reason for the failure should be
425// provided in the |description|.
426static bool ParseFailed(const std::string& line,
427 const std::string& description,
428 SdpParseError* error) {
429 return ParseFailed(line, 0, description, error);
430}
431
432// Parses failure where the failing SDP line isn't know or there are multiple
433// failing lines.
434static bool ParseFailed(const std::string& description, SdpParseError* error) {
435 return ParseFailed("", description, error);
436}
437
438// |line| is the failing line. The failure is due to the fact that |line|
439// doesn't have |expected_fields| fields.
440static bool ParseFailedExpectFieldNum(const std::string& line,
441 int expected_fields,
442 SdpParseError* error) {
443 rtc::StringBuilder description;
444 description << "Expects " << expected_fields << " fields.";
445 return ParseFailed(line, description.str(), error);
446}
447
448// |line| is the failing line. The failure is due to the fact that |line| has
449// less than |expected_min_fields| fields.
450static bool ParseFailedExpectMinFieldNum(const std::string& line,
451 int expected_min_fields,
452 SdpParseError* error) {
453 rtc::StringBuilder description;
454 description << "Expects at least " << expected_min_fields << " fields.";
455 return ParseFailed(line, description.str(), error);
456}
457
458// |line| is the failing line. The failure is due to the fact that it failed to
459// get the value of |attribute|.
460static bool ParseFailedGetValue(const std::string& line,
461 const std::string& attribute,
462 SdpParseError* error) {
463 rtc::StringBuilder description;
464 description << "Failed to get the value of attribute: " << attribute;
465 return ParseFailed(line, description.str(), error);
466}
467
468// The line starting at |line_start| of |message| is the failing line. The
469// failure is due to the line type (e.g. the "m" part of the "m-line")
470// not matching what is expected. The expected line type should be
471// provided as |line_type|.
472static bool ParseFailedExpectLine(const std::string& message,
473 size_t line_start,
474 const char line_type,
475 const std::string& line_value,
476 SdpParseError* error) {
477 rtc::StringBuilder description;
478 description << "Expect line: " << std::string(1, line_type) << "="
479 << line_value;
480 return ParseFailed(message, line_start, description.str(), error);
481}

483static bool AddLine(const std::string& line, std::string* message) {
484 if (!message)
485 return false;
486
487 message->append(line);
488 message->append(kLineBreak);
489 return true;
490}
491
492static bool GetLine(const std::string& message,
493 size_t* pos,
494 std::string* line) {
495 size_t line_begin = *pos;
496 size_t line_end = message.find(kNewLine, line_begin);
497 if (line_end == std::string::npos) {
498 return false;
499 }
500 // Update the new start position
501 *pos = line_end + 1;
502 if (line_end > 0 && (message.at(line_end - 1) == kReturnChar)) {
503 --line_end;
504 }
505 *line = message.substr(line_begin, (line_end - line_begin));
506 const char* cline = line->c_str();
507 // RFC 4566
508 // An SDP session description consists of a number of lines of text of
509 // the form:
510 // <type>=<value>
511 // where <type> MUST be exactly one case-significant character and
512 // <value> is structured text whose format depends on <type>.
513 // Whitespace MUST NOT be used on either side of the "=" sign.
514 //
515 // However, an exception to the whitespace rule is made for "s=", since
516 // RFC4566 also says:
517 //
518 // If a session has no meaningful name, the value "s= " SHOULD be used
519 // (i.e., a single space as the session name).
520 if (line->length() < 3 || !islower(cline[0]) ||
521 cline[1] != kSdpDelimiterEqualChar ||
522 (cline[0] != kLineTypeSessionName &&
523 cline[2] == kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar)) {
524 *pos = line_begin;
525 return false;
526 }
527 return true;
528}
529
530// Init |os| to "|type|=|value|".
531static void InitLine(const char type,
532 const std::string& value,
533 rtc::StringBuilder* os) {
534 os->Clear();
535 *os << std::string(1, type) << kSdpDelimiterEqual << value;
536}
537
538// Init |os| to "a=|attribute|".
539static void InitAttrLine(const std::string& attribute, rtc::StringBuilder* os) {
540 InitLine(kLineTypeAttributes, attribute, os);
541}
542
543// Writes a SDP attribute line based on |attribute| and |value| to |message|.
544static void AddAttributeLine(const std::string& attribute,
545 int value,
546 std::string* message) {
547 rtc::StringBuilder os;
548 InitAttrLine(attribute, &os);
549 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << value;
550 AddLine(os.str(), message);
551}
552
553static bool IsLineType(const std::string& message,
554 const char type,
555 size_t line_start) {
556 if (message.size() < line_start + kLinePrefixLength) {
557 return false;
558 }
559 const char* cmessage = message.c_str();
560 return (cmessage[line_start] == type &&
561 cmessage[line_start + 1] == kSdpDelimiterEqualChar);
562}
563
564static bool IsLineType(const std::string& line, const char type) {
565 return IsLineType(line, type, 0);
566}
567
568static bool GetLineWithType(const std::string& message,
569 size_t* pos,
570 std::string* line,
571 const char type) {
572 if (!IsLineType(message, type, *pos)) {
573 return false;
574 }
575
576 if (!GetLine(message, pos, line))
577 return false;
578
579 return true;
580}
581
582static bool HasAttribute(const std::string& line,
583 const std::string& attribute) {
584 if (line.compare(kLinePrefixLength, attribute.size(), attribute) == 0) {
585 // Make sure that the match is not only a partial match. If length of
586 // strings doesn't match, the next character of the line must be ':' or ' '.
587 // This function is also used for media descriptions (e.g., "m=audio 9..."),
588 // hence the need to also allow space in the end.
589 RTC_CHECK_LE(kLinePrefixLength + attribute.size(), line.size());
590 if ((kLinePrefixLength + attribute.size()) == line.size() ||
591 line[kLinePrefixLength + attribute.size()] == kSdpDelimiterColonChar ||
592 line[kLinePrefixLength + attribute.size()] == kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar) {
593 return true;
594 }
595 }
596 return false;
597}
598
599static bool AddSsrcLine(uint32_t ssrc_id,
600 const std::string& attribute,
601 const std::string& value,
602 std::string* message) {
603 // RFC 5576
604 // a=ssrc:<ssrc-id> <attribute>:<value>
605 rtc::StringBuilder os;
606 InitAttrLine(kAttributeSsrc, &os);
607 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << ssrc_id << kSdpDelimiterSpace << attribute
608 << kSdpDelimiterColon << value;
609 return AddLine(os.str(), message);
610}
611
612// Get value only from <attribute>:<value>.
613static bool GetValue(const std::string& message,
614 const std::string& attribute,
615 std::string* value,
616 SdpParseError* error) {
617 std::string leftpart;
618 if (!rtc::tokenize_first(message, kSdpDelimiterColonChar, &leftpart, value)) {
619 return ParseFailedGetValue(message, attribute, error);
620 }
621 // The left part should end with the expected attribute.
622 if (leftpart.length() < attribute.length() ||
623 leftpart.compare(leftpart.length() - attribute.length(),
624 attribute.length(), attribute) != 0) {
625 return ParseFailedGetValue(message, attribute, error);
626 }
627 return true;
628}
629
630// Get a single [token] from <attribute>:<token>
631static bool GetSingleTokenValue(const std::string& message,
632 const std::string& attribute,
633 std::string* value,
634 SdpParseError* error) {
635 if (!GetValue(message, attribute, value, error)) {
636 return false;
637 }
638 if (strspn(value->c_str(), kLegalTokenCharacters) != value->size()) {
639 rtc::StringBuilder description;
640 description << "Illegal character found in the value of " << attribute;
641 return ParseFailed(message, description.str(), error);
642 }
643 return true;
644}
645
646static bool CaseInsensitiveFind(std::string str1, std::string str2) {
647 absl::c_transform(str1, str1.begin(), ::tolower);
648 absl::c_transform(str2, str2.begin(), ::tolower);
649 return str1.find(str2) != std::string::npos;
650}

652template <class T>
653static bool GetValueFromString(const std::string& line,
654 const std::string& s,
655 T* t,
656 SdpParseError* error) {
657 if (!rtc::FromString(s, t)) {
658 rtc::StringBuilder description;
659 description << "Invalid value: " << s << ".";
660 return ParseFailed(line, description.str(), error);
661 }
662 return true;
663}

665static bool GetPayloadTypeFromString(const std::string& line,
666 const std::string& s,
667 int* payload_type,

669 return GetValueFromString(line, s, payload_type, error) &&
670 cricket::IsValidRtpPayloadType(*payload_type);

673// Creates a StreamParams track in the case when no SSRC lines are signaled.
674// This is a track that does not contain SSRCs and only contains
675// stream_ids/track_id if it's signaled with a=msid lines.
676void CreateTrackWithNoSsrcs(const std::vector<std::string>& msid_stream_ids,
677 const std::string& msid_track_id,
678 const std::vector<RidDescription>& rids,
679 StreamParamsVec* tracks) {
680 StreamParams track;
681 if (msid_track_id.empty() && rids.empty()) {
682 // We only create an unsignaled track if a=msid lines were signaled.
683 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "MSID not signaled, skipping creation of StreamParams";
684 return;
685 }
686 track.set_stream_ids(msid_stream_ids);
687 track.id = msid_track_id;
688 track.set_rids(rids);
689 tracks->push_back(track);
690}
691
692// Creates the StreamParams tracks, for the case when SSRC lines are signaled.
693// |msid_stream_ids| and |msid_track_id| represent the stream/track ID from the
694// "a=msid" attribute, if it exists. They are empty if the attribute does not
695// exist. We prioritize getting stream_ids/track_ids signaled in a=msid lines.
696void CreateTracksFromSsrcInfos(const SsrcInfoVec& ssrc_infos,
697 const std::vector<std::string>& msid_stream_ids,
698 const std::string& msid_track_id,
699 StreamParamsVec* tracks,
700 int msid_signaling) {
701 RTC_DCHECK(tracks != NULL);
702 for (const SsrcInfo& ssrc_info : ssrc_infos) {
703 // According to https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5576#section-6.1, the CNAME
704 // attribute is mandatory, but we relax that restriction.
705 if (ssrc_info.cname.empty()) {
706 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "CNAME attribute missing for SSRC "
707 << ssrc_info.ssrc_id;
708 }
709 std::vector<std::string> stream_ids;
710 std::string track_id;
711 if (msid_signaling & cricket::kMsidSignalingMediaSection) {
712 // This is the case with Unified Plan SDP msid signaling.
713 stream_ids = msid_stream_ids;
714 track_id = msid_track_id;
715 } else if (msid_signaling & cricket::kMsidSignalingSsrcAttribute) {
716 // This is the case with Plan B SDP msid signaling.
717 stream_ids.push_back(ssrc_info.stream_id);
718 track_id = ssrc_info.track_id;
719 } else if (!ssrc_info.mslabel.empty()) {
720 // Since there's no a=msid or a=ssrc msid signaling, this is a sdp from
721 // an older version of client that doesn't support msid.
722 // In that case, we use the mslabel and label to construct the track.
723 stream_ids.push_back(ssrc_info.mslabel);
724 track_id = ssrc_info.label;
725 } else {
726 // Since no media streams isn't supported with older SDP signaling, we
727 // use a default a stream id.
728 stream_ids.push_back(kDefaultMsid);
729 }
730 // If a track ID wasn't populated from the SSRC attributes OR the
731 // msid attribute, use default/random values.
732 if (track_id.empty()) {
733 // TODO(ronghuawu): What should we do if the track id doesn't appear?
734 // Create random string (which will be used as track label later)?
735 track_id = rtc::CreateRandomString(8);
736 }
737
738 auto track_it = absl::c_find_if(
739 *tracks,
740 [track_id](const StreamParams& track) { return track.id == track_id; });
741 if (track_it == tracks->end()) {
742 // If we don't find an existing track, create a new one.
743 tracks->push_back(StreamParams());
744 track_it = tracks->end() - 1;
745 }
746 StreamParams& track = *track_it;
747 track.add_ssrc(ssrc_info.ssrc_id);
748 track.cname = ssrc_info.cname;
749 track.set_stream_ids(stream_ids);
750 track.id = track_id;
751 }
752}
753
754void GetMediaStreamIds(const ContentInfo* content,
755 std::set<std::string>* labels) {
756 for (const StreamParams& stream_params :
757 content->media_description()->streams()) {
758 for (const std::string& stream_id : stream_params.stream_ids()) {
759 labels->insert(stream_id);
760 }
761 }
762}

764// RFC 5245
765// It is RECOMMENDED that default candidates be chosen based on the
766// likelihood of those candidates to work with the peer that is being
767// contacted. It is RECOMMENDED that relayed > reflexive > host.
768static const int kPreferenceUnknown = 0;
769static const int kPreferenceHost = 1;
770static const int kPreferenceReflexive = 2;
771static const int kPreferenceRelayed = 3;
772
773static int GetCandidatePreferenceFromType(const std::string& type) {
774 int preference = kPreferenceUnknown;
775 if (type == cricket::LOCAL_PORT_TYPE) {
776 preference = kPreferenceHost;
777 } else if (type == cricket::STUN_PORT_TYPE) {
778 preference = kPreferenceReflexive;
779 } else if (type == cricket::RELAY_PORT_TYPE) {
780 preference = kPreferenceRelayed;
781 } else {
782 RTC_NOTREACHED();
783 }
784 return preference;
785}
786
787// Get ip and port of the default destination from the |candidates| with the
788// given value of |component_id|. The default candidate should be the one most
789// likely to work, typically IPv4 relay.
790// RFC 5245
791// The value of |component_id| currently supported are 1 (RTP) and 2 (RTCP).
792// TODO(deadbeef): Decide the default destination in webrtcsession and
793// pass it down via SessionDescription.
794static void GetDefaultDestination(const std::vector<Candidate>& candidates,
795 int component_id,
796 std::string* port,
797 std::string* ip,
798 std::string* addr_type) {
799 *addr_type = kConnectionIpv4Addrtype;
800 *port = kDummyPort;
801 *ip = kDummyAddress;
802 int current_preference = kPreferenceUnknown;
803 int current_family = AF_UNSPEC;
804 for (const Candidate& candidate : candidates) {
805 if (candidate.component() != component_id) {
806 continue;
807 }
808 // Default destination should be UDP only.
809 if (candidate.protocol() != cricket::UDP_PROTOCOL_NAME) {
810 continue;
811 }
812 const int preference = GetCandidatePreferenceFromType(candidate.type());
813 const int family = candidate.address().ipaddr().family();
814 // See if this candidate is more preferable then the current one if it's the
815 // same family. Or if the current family is IPv4 already so we could safely
816 // ignore all IPv6 ones. WebRTC bug 4269.
817 // http://code.google.com/p/webrtc/issues/detail?id=4269
818 if ((preference <= current_preference && current_family == family) ||
819 (current_family == AF_INET && family == AF_INET6)) {
820 continue;
821 }
822 if (family == AF_INET) {
823 addr_type->assign(kConnectionIpv4Addrtype);
824 } else if (family == AF_INET6) {
825 addr_type->assign(kConnectionIpv6Addrtype);
826 }
827 current_preference = preference;
828 current_family = family;
829 *port = candidate.address().PortAsString();
830 *ip = candidate.address().ipaddr().ToString();
831 }
832}
833
834// Gets "a=rtcp" line if found default RTCP candidate from |candidates|.
835static std::string GetRtcpLine(const std::vector<Candidate>& candidates) {
836 std::string rtcp_line, rtcp_port, rtcp_ip, addr_type;
837 GetDefaultDestination(candidates, ICE_CANDIDATE_COMPONENT_RTCP, &rtcp_port,
838 &rtcp_ip, &addr_type);
839 // Found default RTCP candidate.
840 // RFC 5245
841 // If the agent is utilizing RTCP, it MUST encode the RTCP candidate
842 // using the a=rtcp attribute as defined in RFC 3605.
843
844 // RFC 3605
845 // rtcp-attribute = "a=rtcp:" port [nettype space addrtype space
846 // connection-address] CRLF
847 rtc::StringBuilder os;
848 InitAttrLine(kAttributeRtcp, &os);
849 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << rtcp_port << " " << kConnectionNettype << " "
850 << addr_type << " " << rtcp_ip;
851 rtcp_line = os.str();
852 return rtcp_line;
853}
854
855// Get candidates according to the mline index from SessionDescriptionInterface.
856static void GetCandidatesByMindex(const SessionDescriptionInterface& desci,
857 int mline_index,
858 std::vector<Candidate>* candidates) {
859 if (!candidates) {
860 return;
861 }
862 const IceCandidateCollection* cc = desci.candidates(mline_index);
863 for (size_t i = 0; i < cc->count(); ++i) {
864 const IceCandidateInterface* candidate = cc->at(i);
865 candidates->push_back(candidate->candidate());
866 }
867}
868
869static bool IsValidPort(int port) {
870 return port >= 0 && port <= 65535;
871}
872
873std::string SdpSerialize(const JsepSessionDescription& jdesc) {
874 const cricket::SessionDescription* desc = jdesc.description();
875 if (!desc) {
876 return "";
877 }
878
879 std::string message;
880
881 // Session Description.
882 AddLine(kSessionVersion, &message);
883 // Session Origin
884 // RFC 4566
885 // o=<username> <sess-id> <sess-version> <nettype> <addrtype>
886 // <unicast-address>
887 rtc::StringBuilder os;
888 InitLine(kLineTypeOrigin, kSessionOriginUsername, &os);
889 const std::string& session_id =
890 jdesc.session_id().empty() ? kSessionOriginSessionId : jdesc.session_id();
891 const std::string& session_version = jdesc.session_version().empty()
892 ? kSessionOriginSessionVersion
893 : jdesc.session_version();
894 os << " " << session_id << " " << session_version << " "
895 << kSessionOriginNettype << " " << kSessionOriginAddrtype << " "
896 << kSessionOriginAddress;
897 AddLine(os.str(), &message);
898 AddLine(kSessionName, &message);
899
900 // Time Description.
901 AddLine(kTimeDescription, &message);
902
903 // BUNDLE Groups
904 std::vector<const cricket::ContentGroup*> groups =
905 desc->GetGroupsByName(cricket::GROUP_TYPE_BUNDLE);
906 for (const cricket::ContentGroup* group : groups) {
907 std::string group_line = kAttrGroup;
908 RTC_DCHECK(group != NULL);
909 for (const std::string& content_name : group->content_names()) {
910 group_line.append(" ");
911 group_line.append(content_name);
912 }
913 AddLine(group_line, &message);
914 }
915
916 // Mixed one- and two-byte header extension.
917 if (desc->extmap_allow_mixed()) {
918 InitAttrLine(kAttributeExtmapAllowMixed, &os);
919 AddLine(os.str(), &message);
920 }
921
922 // MediaStream semantics
923 InitAttrLine(kAttributeMsidSemantics, &os);
924 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << " " << kMediaStreamSemantic;
925
926 std::set<std::string> media_stream_ids;
927 const ContentInfo* audio_content = GetFirstAudioContent(desc);
928 if (audio_content)
929 GetMediaStreamIds(audio_content, &media_stream_ids);
930
931 const ContentInfo* video_content = GetFirstVideoContent(desc);
932 if (video_content)
933 GetMediaStreamIds(video_content, &media_stream_ids);
934
935 for (const std::string& id : media_stream_ids) {
936 os << " " << id;
937 }
938 AddLine(os.str(), &message);
939
940 // a=ice-lite
941 //
942 // TODO(deadbeef): It's weird that we need to iterate TransportInfos for
943 // this, when it's a session-level attribute. It really should be moved to a
944 // session-level structure like SessionDescription.
945 for (const cricket::TransportInfo& transport : desc->transport_infos()) {
946 if (transport.description.ice_mode == cricket::ICEMODE_LITE) {
947 InitAttrLine(kAttributeIceLite, &os);
948 AddLine(os.str(), &message);
949 break;
950 }
951 }
952
953 // Preserve the order of the media contents.
954 int mline_index = -1;
955 for (const ContentInfo& content : desc->contents()) {
956 std::vector<Candidate> candidates;
957 GetCandidatesByMindex(jdesc, ++mline_index, &candidates);
958 BuildMediaDescription(&content, desc->GetTransportInfoByName(content.name),
959 content.media_description()->type(), candidates,
960 desc->msid_signaling(), &message);
961 }
962 return message;
963}

965// Serializes the passed in IceCandidateInterface to a SDP string.
966// candidate - The candidate to be serialized.
967std::string SdpSerializeCandidate(const IceCandidateInterface& candidate) {
968 return SdpSerializeCandidate(candidate.candidate());
969}
970
971// Serializes a cricket Candidate.
972std::string SdpSerializeCandidate(const cricket::Candidate& candidate) {
973 std::string message;
974 std::vector<cricket::Candidate> candidates(1, candidate);
975 BuildCandidate(candidates, true, &message);
976 // From WebRTC draft section 4.8.1.1 candidate-attribute will be
977 // just candidate:<candidate> not a=candidate:<blah>CRLF
978 RTC_DCHECK(message.find("a=") == 0);
979 message.erase(0, 2);
980 RTC_DCHECK(message.find(kLineBreak) == message.size() - 2);
981 message.resize(message.size() - 2);
982 return message;
983}
984
985bool SdpDeserialize(const std::string& message,
986 JsepSessionDescription* jdesc,
987 SdpParseError* error) {
988 std::string session_id;
989 std::string session_version;
990 TransportDescription session_td("", "");
991 RtpHeaderExtensions session_extmaps;
992 rtc::SocketAddress session_connection_addr;
993 auto desc = std::make_unique<cricket::SessionDescription>();
994 size_t current_pos = 0;
995
996 // Session Description
997 if (!ParseSessionDescription(message, &current_pos, &session_id,
998 &session_version, &session_td, &session_extmaps,
999 &session_connection_addr, desc.get(), error)) {
1000 return false;
1001 }
1002
1003 // Media Description
1004 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<JsepIceCandidate>> candidates;
1005 if (!ParseMediaDescription(message, session_td, session_extmaps, &current_pos,
1006 session_connection_addr, desc.get(), &candidates,
1007 error)) {
1008 return false;
1009 }
1010
1011 jdesc->Initialize(std::move(desc), session_id, session_version);
1012
1013 for (const auto& candidate : candidates) {
1014 jdesc->AddCandidate(candidate.get());
1015 }
1016 return true;
1017}

1019bool SdpDeserializeCandidate(const std::string& message,
1020 JsepIceCandidate* jcandidate,
1021 SdpParseError* error) {
1022 RTC_DCHECK(jcandidate != NULL);
1023 Candidate candidate;
1024 if (!ParseCandidate(message, &candidate, error, true)) {
1025 return false;
1026 }
1027 jcandidate->SetCandidate(candidate);
1028 return true;
1029}

1031bool SdpDeserializeCandidate(const std::string& transport_name,
1032 const std::string& message,
1033 cricket::Candidate* candidate,
1034 SdpParseError* error) {
1035 RTC_DCHECK(candidate != nullptr);
1036 if (!ParseCandidate(message, candidate, error, true)) {
1037 return false;
1038 }
1039 candidate->set_transport_name(transport_name);
1040 return true;
1041}
1042
1043bool ParseCandidate(const std::string& message,
1044 Candidate* candidate,
1045 SdpParseError* error,
1046 bool is_raw) {
1047 RTC_DCHECK(candidate != NULL);
1048
1049 // Get the first line from |message|.
1050 std::string first_line = message;
1051 size_t pos = 0;
1052 GetLine(message, &pos, &first_line);
1053
1054 // Makes sure |message| contains only one line.
1055 if (message.size() > first_line.size()) {
1056 std::string left, right;
1057 if (rtc::tokenize_first(message, kNewLineChar, &left, &right) &&
1058 !right.empty()) {
1059 return ParseFailed(message, 0, "Expect one line only", error);
1060 }
1061 }
1062
1063 // From WebRTC draft section 4.8.1.1 candidate-attribute should be
1064 // candidate:<candidate> when trickled, but we still support
1065 // a=candidate:<blah>CRLF for backward compatibility and for parsing a line
1066 // from the SDP.
1067 if (IsLineType(first_line, kLineTypeAttributes)) {
1068 first_line = first_line.substr(kLinePrefixLength);
1069 }
1070
1071 std::string attribute_candidate;
1072 std::string candidate_value;
1073
1074 // |first_line| must be in the form of "candidate:<value>".
1075 if (!rtc::tokenize_first(first_line, kSdpDelimiterColonChar,
1076 &attribute_candidate, &candidate_value) ||
1077 attribute_candidate != kAttributeCandidate) {
1078 if (is_raw) {
1079 rtc::StringBuilder description;
1080 description << "Expect line: " << kAttributeCandidate
1081 << ":"
1082 "<candidate-str>";
1083 return ParseFailed(first_line, 0, description.str(), error);
1084 } else {
1085 return ParseFailedExpectLine(first_line, 0, kLineTypeAttributes,
1086 kAttributeCandidate, error);
1087 }
1088 }
1089
1090 std::vector<std::string> fields;
1091 rtc::split(candidate_value, kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &fields);
1092
1093 // RFC 5245
1094 // a=candidate:<foundation> <component-id> <transport> <priority>
1095 // <connection-address> <port> typ <candidate-types>
1096 // [raddr <connection-address>] [rport <port>]
1097 // *(SP extension-att-name SP extension-att-value)
1098 const size_t expected_min_fields = 8;
1099 if (fields.size() < expected_min_fields ||
1100 (fields[6] != kAttributeCandidateTyp)) {
1101 return ParseFailedExpectMinFieldNum(first_line, expected_min_fields, error);
1102 }
1103 const std::string& foundation = fields[0];
1104
1105 int component_id = 0;
1106 if (!GetValueFromString(first_line, fields[1], &component_id, error)) {
1107 return false;
1108 }
1109 const std::string& transport = fields[2];
1110 uint32_t priority = 0;
1111 if (!GetValueFromString(first_line, fields[3], &priority, error)) {
1112 return false;
1113 }
1114 const std::string& connection_address = fields[4];
1115 int port = 0;
1116 if (!GetValueFromString(first_line, fields[5], &port, error)) {
1117 return false;
1118 }
1119 if (!IsValidPort(port)) {
1120 return ParseFailed(first_line, "Invalid port number.", error);
1121 }
1122 SocketAddress address(connection_address, port);
1123
1124 cricket::ProtocolType protocol;
1125 if (!StringToProto(transport.c_str(), &protocol)) {
1126 return ParseFailed(first_line, "Unsupported transport type.", error);
1127 }
1128 bool tcp_protocol = false;
1129 switch (protocol) {
1130 // Supported protocols.
1131 case cricket::PROTO_UDP:
1132 break;
1133 case cricket::PROTO_TCP:
1134 case cricket::PROTO_SSLTCP:
1135 tcp_protocol = true;
1136 break;
1137 default:
1138 return ParseFailed(first_line, "Unsupported transport type.", error);
1139 }
1140
1141 std::string candidate_type;
1142 const std::string& type = fields[7];
1143 if (type == kCandidateHost) {
1144 candidate_type = cricket::LOCAL_PORT_TYPE;
1145 } else if (type == kCandidateSrflx) {
1146 candidate_type = cricket::STUN_PORT_TYPE;
1147 } else if (type == kCandidateRelay) {
1148 candidate_type = cricket::RELAY_PORT_TYPE;
1149 } else if (type == kCandidatePrflx) {
1150 candidate_type = cricket::PRFLX_PORT_TYPE;
1151 } else {
1152 return ParseFailed(first_line, "Unsupported candidate type.", error);
1153 }
1154
1155 size_t current_position = expected_min_fields;
1156 SocketAddress related_address;
1157 // The 2 optional fields for related address
1158 // [raddr <connection-address>] [rport <port>]
1159 if (fields.size() >= (current_position + 2) &&
1160 fields[current_position] == kAttributeCandidateRaddr) {
1161 related_address.SetIP(fields[++current_position]);
1162 ++current_position;
1163 }
1164 if (fields.size() >= (current_position + 2) &&
1165 fields[current_position] == kAttributeCandidateRport) {
1166 int port = 0;
1167 if (!GetValueFromString(first_line, fields[++current_position], &port,
1168 error)) {
1169 return false;
1170 }
1171 if (!IsValidPort(port)) {
1172 return ParseFailed(first_line, "Invalid port number.", error);
1173 }
1174 related_address.SetPort(port);
1175 ++current_position;
1176 }
1177
1178 // If this is a TCP candidate, it has additional extension as defined in
1179 // RFC 6544.
1180 std::string tcptype;
1181 if (fields.size() >= (current_position + 2) &&
1182 fields[current_position] == kTcpCandidateType) {
1183 tcptype = fields[++current_position];
1184 ++current_position;
1185
1186 if (tcptype != cricket::TCPTYPE_ACTIVE_STR &&
1187 tcptype != cricket::TCPTYPE_PASSIVE_STR &&
1188 tcptype != cricket::TCPTYPE_SIMOPEN_STR) {
1189 return ParseFailed(first_line, "Invalid TCP candidate type.", error);
1190 }
1191
1192 if (!tcp_protocol) {
1193 return ParseFailed(first_line, "Invalid non-TCP candidate", error);
1194 }
1195 } else if (tcp_protocol) {
1196 // We allow the tcptype to be missing, for backwards compatibility,
1197 // treating it as a passive candidate.
1198 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11466): Treat a missing tcptype as an error?
1199 tcptype = cricket::TCPTYPE_PASSIVE_STR;
1200 }
1201
1202 // Extension
1203 // Though non-standard, we support the ICE ufrag and pwd being signaled on
1204 // the candidate to avoid issues with confusing which generation a candidate
1205 // belongs to when trickling multiple generations at the same time.
1206 std::string username;
1207 std::string password;
1208 uint32_t generation = 0;
1209 uint16_t network_id = 0;
1210 uint16_t network_cost = 0;
1211 for (size_t i = current_position; i + 1 < fields.size(); ++i) {
1212 // RFC 5245
1213 // *(SP extension-att-name SP extension-att-value)
1214 if (fields[i] == kAttributeCandidateGeneration) {
1215 if (!GetValueFromString(first_line, fields[++i], &generation, error)) {
1216 return false;
1217 }
1218 } else if (fields[i] == kAttributeCandidateUfrag) {
1219 username = fields[++i];
1220 } else if (fields[i] == kAttributeCandidatePwd) {
1221 password = fields[++i];
1222 } else if (fields[i] == kAttributeCandidateNetworkId) {
1223 if (!GetValueFromString(first_line, fields[++i], &network_id, error)) {
1224 return false;
1225 }
1226 } else if (fields[i] == kAttributeCandidateNetworkCost) {
1227 if (!GetValueFromString(first_line, fields[++i], &network_cost, error)) {
1228 return false;
1229 }
1230 network_cost = std::min(network_cost, rtc::kNetworkCostMax);
1231 } else {
1232 // Skip the unknown extension.
1233 ++i;
1234 }
1235 }
1236
1237 *candidate = Candidate(component_id, cricket::ProtoToString(protocol),
1238 address, priority, username, password, candidate_type,
1239 generation, foundation, network_id, network_cost);
1240 candidate->set_related_address(related_address);
1241 candidate->set_tcptype(tcptype);
1242 return true;
1243}
1244
1245bool ParseIceOptions(const std::string& line,
1246 std::vector<std::string>* transport_options,
1247 SdpParseError* error) {
1248 std::string ice_options;
1249 if (!GetValue(line, kAttributeIceOption, &ice_options, error)) {
1250 return false;
1251 }
1252 std::vector<std::string> fields;
1253 rtc::split(ice_options, kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &fields);
1254 for (size_t i = 0; i < fields.size(); ++i) {
1255 transport_options->push_back(fields[i]);
1256 }
1257 return true;
1258}
1259
1260bool ParseSctpPort(const std::string& line,
1261 int* sctp_port,
1262 SdpParseError* error) {
1263 // draft-ietf-mmusic-sctp-sdp-26
1264 // a=sctp-port
1265 std::vector<std::string> fields;
1266 const size_t expected_min_fields = 2;
1267 rtc::split(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength), kSdpDelimiterColonChar, &fields);
1268 if (fields.size() < expected_min_fields) {
1269 fields.resize(0);
1270 rtc::split(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength), kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &fields);
1271 }
1272 if (fields.size() < expected_min_fields) {
1273 return ParseFailedExpectMinFieldNum(line, expected_min_fields, error);
1274 }
1275 if (!rtc::FromString(fields[1], sctp_port)) {
1276 return ParseFailed(line, "Invalid sctp port value.", error);
1277 }
1278 return true;
1279}
1280
1281bool ParseSctpMaxMessageSize(const std::string& line,
1282 int* max_message_size,
1283 SdpParseError* error) {
1284 // draft-ietf-mmusic-sctp-sdp-26
1285 // a=max-message-size:199999
1286 std::vector<std::string> fields;
1287 const size_t expected_min_fields = 2;
1288 rtc::split(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength), kSdpDelimiterColonChar, &fields);
1289 if (fields.size() < expected_min_fields) {
1290 return ParseFailedExpectMinFieldNum(line, expected_min_fields, error);
1291 }
1292 if (!rtc::FromString(fields[1], max_message_size)) {
1293 return ParseFailed(line, "Invalid SCTP max message size.", error);
1294 }
1295 return true;
1296}
1297
1298bool ParseExtmap(const std::string& line,
1299 RtpExtension* extmap,
1300 SdpParseError* error) {
1301 // RFC 5285
1302 // a=extmap:<value>["/"<direction>] <URI> <extensionattributes>
1303 std::vector<std::string> fields;
1304 rtc::split(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength), kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &fields);
1305 const size_t expected_min_fields = 2;
1306 if (fields.size() < expected_min_fields) {
1307 return ParseFailedExpectMinFieldNum(line, expected_min_fields, error);
1308 }
1309 std::string uri = fields[1];
1310
1311 std::string value_direction;
1312 if (!GetValue(fields[0], kAttributeExtmap, &value_direction, error)) {
1313 return false;
1314 }
1315 std::vector<std::string> sub_fields;
1316 rtc::split(value_direction, kSdpDelimiterSlashChar, &sub_fields);
1317 int value = 0;
1318 if (!GetValueFromString(line, sub_fields[0], &value, error)) {
1319 return false;
1320 }
1321
1322 bool encrypted = false;
1323 if (uri == RtpExtension::kEncryptHeaderExtensionsUri) {
1324 // RFC 6904
1325 // a=extmap:<value["/"<direction>] urn:ietf:params:rtp-hdrext:encrypt <URI>
1326 // <extensionattributes>
1327 const size_t expected_min_fields_encrypted = expected_min_fields + 1;
1328 if (fields.size() < expected_min_fields_encrypted) {
1329 return ParseFailedExpectMinFieldNum(line, expected_min_fields_encrypted,
1330 error);
1331 }
1332
1333 encrypted = true;
1334 uri = fields[2];
1335 if (uri == RtpExtension::kEncryptHeaderExtensionsUri) {
1336 return ParseFailed(line, "Recursive encrypted header.", error);
1337 }
1338 }
1339
1340 *extmap = RtpExtension(uri, value, encrypted);
1341 return true;
1342}
1343
1344static void BuildSctpContentAttributes(
1345 std::string* message,
1346 const cricket::SctpDataContentDescription* data_desc) {
1347 rtc::StringBuilder os;
1348 if (data_desc->use_sctpmap()) {
1349 // draft-ietf-mmusic-sctp-sdp-04
1350 // a=sctpmap:sctpmap-number protocol [streams]
1351 rtc::StringBuilder os;
1352 InitAttrLine(kAttributeSctpmap, &os);
1353 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << data_desc->port() << kSdpDelimiterSpace
1354 << kDefaultSctpmapProtocol << kSdpDelimiterSpace
1355 << cricket::kMaxSctpStreams;
1356 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1357 } else {
1358 // draft-ietf-mmusic-sctp-sdp-23
1359 // a=sctp-port:<port>
1360 InitAttrLine(kAttributeSctpPort, &os);
1361 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << data_desc->port();
1362 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1363 if (data_desc->max_message_size() != kDefaultSctpMaxMessageSize) {
1364 InitAttrLine(kAttributeMaxMessageSize, &os);
1365 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << data_desc->max_message_size();
1366 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1367 }
1368 }
1369}
1370
1371void BuildMediaDescription(const ContentInfo* content_info,
1372 const TransportInfo* transport_info,
1373 const cricket::MediaType media_type,
1374 const std::vector<Candidate>& candidates,
1375 int msid_signaling,
1376 std::string* message) {
1377 RTC_DCHECK(message != NULL);
1378 if (content_info == NULL || message == NULL) {
1379 return;
1380 }
1381 rtc::StringBuilder os;
1382 const MediaContentDescription* media_desc = content_info->media_description();
1383 RTC_DCHECK(media_desc);
1384
1385 // RFC 4566
1386 // m=<media> <port> <proto> <fmt>
1387 // fmt is a list of payload type numbers that MAY be used in the session.
1388 std::string type;
1389 std::string fmt;
1390 if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
1391 type = kMediaTypeVideo;
1392 const VideoContentDescription* video_desc = media_desc->as_video();
1393 for (const cricket::VideoCodec& codec : video_desc->codecs()) {
1394 fmt.append(" ");
1395 fmt.append(rtc::ToString(codec.id));
1396 }
1397 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
1398 type = kMediaTypeAudio;
1399 const AudioContentDescription* audio_desc = media_desc->as_audio();
1400 for (const cricket::AudioCodec& codec : audio_desc->codecs()) {
1401 fmt.append(" ");
1402 fmt.append(rtc::ToString(codec.id));
1403 }
1404 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_DATA) {
1405 type = kMediaTypeData;
1406 const cricket::SctpDataContentDescription* sctp_data_desc =
1407 media_desc->as_sctp();
1408 if (sctp_data_desc) {
1409 fmt.append(" ");
1410
1411 if (sctp_data_desc->use_sctpmap()) {
1412 fmt.append(rtc::ToString(sctp_data_desc->port()));
1413 } else {
1414 fmt.append(kDefaultSctpmapProtocol);
1415 }
1416 } else {
1417 RTC_NOTREACHED() << "Data description without SCTP";
1418 }
1419 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_UNSUPPORTED) {
1420 const UnsupportedContentDescription* unsupported_desc =
1421 media_desc->as_unsupported();
1422 type = unsupported_desc->media_type();
1423 } else {
1424 RTC_NOTREACHED();
1425 }
1426 // The fmt must never be empty. If no codecs are found, set the fmt attribute
1427 // to 0.
1428 if (fmt.empty()) {
1429 fmt = " 0";
1430 }
1431
1432 // The port number in the m line will be updated later when associated with
1433 // the candidates.
1434 //
1435 // A port value of 0 indicates that the m= section is rejected.
1436 // RFC 3264
1437 // To reject an offered stream, the port number in the corresponding stream in
1438 // the answer MUST be set to zero.
1439 //
1440 // However, the BUNDLE draft adds a new meaning to port zero, when used along
1441 // with a=bundle-only.
1442 std::string port = kDummyPort;
1443 if (content_info->rejected || content_info->bundle_only) {
1444 port = kMediaPortRejected;
1445 } else if (!media_desc->connection_address().IsNil()) {
1446 port = rtc::ToString(media_desc->connection_address().port());
1447 }
1448
1449 rtc::SSLFingerprint* fp =
1450 (transport_info) ? transport_info->description.identity_fingerprint.get()
1451 : NULL;
1452
1453 // Add the m and c lines.
1454 InitLine(kLineTypeMedia, type, &os);
1455 os << " " << port << " " << media_desc->protocol() << fmt;
1456 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1457
1458 InitLine(kLineTypeConnection, kConnectionNettype, &os);
1459 if (media_desc->connection_address().IsNil()) {
1460 os << " " << kConnectionIpv4Addrtype << " " << kDummyAddress;
1461 } else if (media_desc->connection_address().family() == AF_INET) {
1462 os << " " << kConnectionIpv4Addrtype << " "
1463 << media_desc->connection_address().ipaddr().ToString();
1464 } else if (media_desc->connection_address().family() == AF_INET6) {
1465 os << " " << kConnectionIpv6Addrtype << " "
1466 << media_desc->connection_address().ipaddr().ToString();
1467 } else {
1468 os << " " << kConnectionIpv4Addrtype << " " << kDummyAddress;
1469 }
1470 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1471
1472 // RFC 4566
1473 // b=AS:<bandwidth> or
1474 // b=TIAS:<bandwidth>
1475 int bandwidth = media_desc->bandwidth();
1476 std::string bandwidth_type = media_desc->bandwidth_type();
1477 if (bandwidth_type == kApplicationSpecificBandwidth && bandwidth >= 1000) {
1478 InitLine(kLineTypeSessionBandwidth, bandwidth_type, &os);
1479 bandwidth /= 1000;
1480 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << bandwidth;
1481 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1482 } else if (bandwidth_type == kTransportSpecificBandwidth && bandwidth > 0) {
1483 InitLine(kLineTypeSessionBandwidth, bandwidth_type, &os);
1484 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << bandwidth;
1485 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1486 }
1487
1488 // Add the a=bundle-only line.
1489 if (content_info->bundle_only) {
1490 InitAttrLine(kAttributeBundleOnly, &os);
1491 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1492 }
1493
1494 // Add the a=rtcp line.
1495 if (cricket::IsRtpProtocol(media_desc->protocol())) {
1496 std::string rtcp_line = GetRtcpLine(candidates);
1497 if (!rtcp_line.empty()) {
1498 AddLine(rtcp_line, message);
1499 }
1500 }
1501
1502 // Build the a=candidate lines. We don't include ufrag and pwd in the
1503 // candidates in the SDP to avoid redundancy.
1504 BuildCandidate(candidates, false, message);
1505
1506 // Use the transport_info to build the media level ice-ufrag and ice-pwd.
1507 if (transport_info) {
1508 // RFC 5245
1509 // ice-pwd-att = "ice-pwd" ":" password
1510 // ice-ufrag-att = "ice-ufrag" ":" ufrag
1511 // ice-ufrag
1512 if (!transport_info->description.ice_ufrag.empty()) {
1513 InitAttrLine(kAttributeIceUfrag, &os);
1514 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << transport_info->description.ice_ufrag;
1515 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1516 }
1517 // ice-pwd
1518 if (!transport_info->description.ice_pwd.empty()) {
1519 InitAttrLine(kAttributeIcePwd, &os);
1520 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << transport_info->description.ice_pwd;
1521 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1522 }
1523
1524 // draft-petithuguenin-mmusic-ice-attributes-level-03
1525 BuildIceOptions(transport_info->description.transport_options, message);
1526
1527 // RFC 4572
1528 // fingerprint-attribute =
1529 // "fingerprint" ":" hash-func SP fingerprint
1530 if (fp) {
1531 // Insert the fingerprint attribute.
1532 InitAttrLine(kAttributeFingerprint, &os);
1533 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << fp->algorithm << kSdpDelimiterSpace
1534 << fp->GetRfc4572Fingerprint();
1535 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1536
1537 // Inserting setup attribute.
1538 if (transport_info->description.connection_role !=
1539 cricket::CONNECTIONROLE_NONE) {
1540 // Making sure we are not using "passive" mode.
1541 cricket::ConnectionRole role =
1542 transport_info->description.connection_role;
1543 std::string dtls_role_str;
1544 const bool success =
1545 cricket::ConnectionRoleToString(role, &dtls_role_str);
1546 RTC_DCHECK(success);
1547 InitAttrLine(kAttributeSetup, &os);
1548 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << dtls_role_str;
1549 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1550 }
1551 }
1552 }
1553
1554 // RFC 3388
1555 // mid-attribute = "a=mid:" identification-tag
1556 // identification-tag = token
1557 // Use the content name as the mid identification-tag.
1558 InitAttrLine(kAttributeMid, &os);
1559 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << content_info->name;
1560 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1561
1562 if (cricket::IsDtlsSctp(media_desc->protocol())) {
1563 const cricket::SctpDataContentDescription* data_desc =
1564 media_desc->as_sctp();
1565 BuildSctpContentAttributes(message, data_desc);
1566 } else if (cricket::IsRtpProtocol(media_desc->protocol())) {
1567 BuildRtpContentAttributes(media_desc, media_type, msid_signaling, message);
1568 }
1569}
1570
1571void BuildRtpContentAttributes(const MediaContentDescription* media_desc,
1572 const cricket::MediaType media_type,
1573 int msid_signaling,
1574 std::string* message) {
1575 SdpSerializer serializer;
1576 rtc::StringBuilder os;
1577 // RFC 8285
1578 // a=extmap-allow-mixed
1579 // The attribute MUST be either on session level or media level. We support
1580 // responding on both levels, however, we don't respond on media level if it's
1581 // set on session level.
1582 if (media_desc->extmap_allow_mixed_enum() ==
1583 MediaContentDescription::kMedia) {
1584 InitAttrLine(kAttributeExtmapAllowMixed, &os);
1585 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1586 }
1587 // RFC 8285
1588 // a=extmap:<value>["/"<direction>] <URI> <extensionattributes>
1589 // The definitions MUST be either all session level or all media level. This
1590 // implementation uses all media level.
1591 for (size_t i = 0; i < media_desc->rtp_header_extensions().size(); ++i) {
1592 const RtpExtension& extension = media_desc->rtp_header_extensions()[i];
1593 InitAttrLine(kAttributeExtmap, &os);
1594 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << extension.id;
1595 if (extension.encrypt) {
1596 os << kSdpDelimiterSpace << RtpExtension::kEncryptHeaderExtensionsUri;
1597 }
1598 os << kSdpDelimiterSpace << extension.uri;
1599 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1600 }
1601
1602 // RFC 3264
1603 // a=sendrecv || a=sendonly || a=sendrecv || a=inactive
1604 switch (media_desc->direction()) {
1605 // Special case that for sdp purposes should be treated same as inactive.
1606 case RtpTransceiverDirection::kStopped:
1607 case RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive:
1608 InitAttrLine(kAttributeInactive, &os);
1609 break;
1610 case RtpTransceiverDirection::kSendOnly:
1611 InitAttrLine(kAttributeSendOnly, &os);
1612 break;
1613 case RtpTransceiverDirection::kRecvOnly:
1614 InitAttrLine(kAttributeRecvOnly, &os);
1615 break;
1616 case RtpTransceiverDirection::kSendRecv:
1617 InitAttrLine(kAttributeSendRecv, &os);
1618 break;
1619 default:
1620 RTC_NOTREACHED();
1621 InitAttrLine(kAttributeSendRecv, &os);
1622 break;
1623 }
1624 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1625
1626 // Specified in https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-mmusic-msid/16/
1627 // a=msid:<msid-id> <msid-appdata>
1628 // The msid-id is a 1*64 token char representing the media stream id, and the
1629 // msid-appdata is a 1*64 token char representing the track id. There is a
1630 // line for every media stream, with a special msid-id value of "-"
1631 // representing no streams. The value of "msid-appdata" MUST be identical for
1632 // all lines.
1633 if (msid_signaling & cricket::kMsidSignalingMediaSection) {
1634 const StreamParamsVec& streams = media_desc->streams();
1635 if (streams.size() == 1u) {
1636 const StreamParams& track = streams[0];
1637 std::vector<std::string> stream_ids = track.stream_ids();
1638 if (stream_ids.empty()) {
1639 stream_ids.push_back(kNoStreamMsid);
1640 }
1641 for (const std::string& stream_id : stream_ids) {
1642 InitAttrLine(kAttributeMsid, &os);
1643 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << stream_id << kSdpDelimiterSpace << track.id;
1644 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1645 }
1646 } else if (streams.size() > 1u) {
1647 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
1648 << "Trying to serialize Unified Plan SDP with more than "
1649 "one track in a media section. Omitting 'a=msid'.";
1650 }
1651 }
1652
1653 // RFC 5761
1654 // a=rtcp-mux
1655 if (media_desc->rtcp_mux()) {
1656 InitAttrLine(kAttributeRtcpMux, &os);
1657 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1658 }
1659
1660 // RFC 5506
1661 // a=rtcp-rsize
1662 if (media_desc->rtcp_reduced_size()) {
1663 InitAttrLine(kAttributeRtcpReducedSize, &os);
1664 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1665 }
1666
1667 if (media_desc->conference_mode()) {
1668 InitAttrLine(kAttributeXGoogleFlag, &os);
1669 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << kValueConference;
1670 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1671 }
1672
1673 if (media_desc->remote_estimate()) {
1674 InitAttrLine(kAttributeRtcpRemoteEstimate, &os);
1675 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1676 }
1677
1678 // RFC 4568
1679 // a=crypto:<tag> <crypto-suite> <key-params> [<session-params>]
1680 for (const CryptoParams& crypto_params : media_desc->cryptos()) {
1681 InitAttrLine(kAttributeCrypto, &os);
1682 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << crypto_params.tag << " "
1683 << crypto_params.cipher_suite << " " << crypto_params.key_params;
1684 if (!crypto_params.session_params.empty()) {
1685 os << " " << crypto_params.session_params;
1686 }
1687 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1688 }
1689
1690 // RFC 4566
1691 // a=rtpmap:<payload type> <encoding name>/<clock rate>
1692 // [/<encodingparameters>]
1693 BuildRtpMap(media_desc, media_type, message);
1694
1695 for (const StreamParams& track : media_desc->streams()) {
1696 // Build the ssrc-group lines.
1697 for (const SsrcGroup& ssrc_group : track.ssrc_groups) {
1698 // RFC 5576
1699 // a=ssrc-group:<semantics> <ssrc-id> ...
1700 if (ssrc_group.ssrcs.empty()) {
1701 continue;
1702 }
1703 InitAttrLine(kAttributeSsrcGroup, &os);
1704 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << ssrc_group.semantics;
1705 for (uint32_t ssrc : ssrc_group.ssrcs) {
1706 os << kSdpDelimiterSpace << rtc::ToString(ssrc);
1707 }
1708 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1709 }
1710 // Build the ssrc lines for each ssrc.
1711 for (uint32_t ssrc : track.ssrcs) {
1712 // RFC 5576
1713 // a=ssrc:<ssrc-id> cname:<value>
1714 AddSsrcLine(ssrc, kSsrcAttributeCname, track.cname, message);
1715
1716 if (msid_signaling & cricket::kMsidSignalingSsrcAttribute) {
1717 // draft-alvestrand-mmusic-msid-00
1718 // a=ssrc:<ssrc-id> msid:identifier [appdata]
1719 // The appdata consists of the "id" attribute of a MediaStreamTrack,
1720 // which corresponds to the "id" attribute of StreamParams.
1721 // Since a=ssrc msid signaling is used in Plan B SDP semantics, and
1722 // multiple stream ids are not supported for Plan B, we are only adding
1723 // a line for the first media stream id here.
1724 const std::string& track_stream_id = track.first_stream_id();
1725 // We use a special msid-id value of "-" to represent no streams,
1726 // for Unified Plan compatibility. Plan B will always have a
1727 // track_stream_id.
1728 const std::string& stream_id =
1729 track_stream_id.empty() ? kNoStreamMsid : track_stream_id;
1730 InitAttrLine(kAttributeSsrc, &os);
1731 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << ssrc << kSdpDelimiterSpace
1732 << kSsrcAttributeMsid << kSdpDelimiterColon << stream_id
1733 << kSdpDelimiterSpace << track.id;
1734 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1735
1736 // TODO(ronghuawu): Remove below code which is for backward
1737 // compatibility.
1738 // draft-alvestrand-rtcweb-mid-01
1739 // a=ssrc:<ssrc-id> mslabel:<value>
1740 // The label isn't yet defined.
1741 // a=ssrc:<ssrc-id> label:<value>
1742 AddSsrcLine(ssrc, kSsrcAttributeMslabel, stream_id, message);
1743 AddSsrcLine(ssrc, kSSrcAttributeLabel, track.id, message);
1744 }
1745 }
1746
1747 // Build the rid lines for each layer of the track
1748 for (const RidDescription& rid_description : track.rids()) {
1749 InitAttrLine(kAttributeRid, &os);
1750 os << kSdpDelimiterColon
1751 << serializer.SerializeRidDescription(rid_description);
1752 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1753 }
1754 }
1755
1756 for (const RidDescription& rid_description : media_desc->receive_rids()) {
1757 InitAttrLine(kAttributeRid, &os);
1758 os << kSdpDelimiterColon
1759 << serializer.SerializeRidDescription(rid_description);
1760 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1761 }
1762
1763 // Simulcast (a=simulcast)
1764 // https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-mmusic-sdp-simulcast-13#section-5.1
1765 if (media_desc->HasSimulcast()) {
1766 const auto& simulcast = media_desc->simulcast_description();
1767 InitAttrLine(kAttributeSimulcast, &os);
1768 os << kSdpDelimiterColon
1769 << serializer.SerializeSimulcastDescription(simulcast);
1770 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1771 }
1772}

1774void WriteFmtpHeader(int payload_type, rtc::StringBuilder* os) {
1775 // fmtp header: a=fmtp:|payload_type| <parameters>
1776 // Add a=fmtp
1777 InitAttrLine(kAttributeFmtp, os);
1778 // Add :|payload_type|
1779 *os << kSdpDelimiterColon << payload_type;
1780}

1782void WritePacketizationHeader(int payload_type, rtc::StringBuilder* os) {
1783 // packetization header: a=packetization:|payload_type| <packetization_format>
1784 // Add a=packetization
1785 InitAttrLine(kAttributePacketization, os);
1786 // Add :|payload_type|
1787 *os << kSdpDelimiterColon << payload_type;
1788}
1789
1790void WriteRtcpFbHeader(int payload_type, rtc::StringBuilder* os) {
1791 // rtcp-fb header: a=rtcp-fb:|payload_type|
1792 // <parameters>/<ccm <ccm_parameters>>
1793 // Add a=rtcp-fb
1794 InitAttrLine(kAttributeRtcpFb, os);
1795 // Add :
1796 *os << kSdpDelimiterColon;
1797 if (payload_type == kWildcardPayloadType) {
1798 *os << "*";
1799 } else {
1800 *os << payload_type;
1801 }
1802}
1803
1804void WriteFmtpParameter(const std::string& parameter_name,
1805 const std::string& parameter_value,
1806 rtc::StringBuilder* os) {
1807 if (parameter_name == "") {
1808 // RFC 2198 and RFC 4733 don't use key-value pairs.
1809 *os << parameter_value;
1810 } else {
1811 // fmtp parameters: |parameter_name|=|parameter_value|
1812 *os << parameter_name << kSdpDelimiterEqual << parameter_value;
1813 }
1814}
1815
1816bool IsFmtpParam(const std::string& name) {
1817 // RFC 4855, section 3 specifies the mapping of media format parameters to SDP
1818 // parameters. Only ptime, maxptime, channels and rate are placed outside of
1819 // the fmtp line. In WebRTC, channels and rate are already handled separately
1820 // and thus not included in the CodecParameterMap.
1821 return name != kCodecParamPTime && name != kCodecParamMaxPTime;
1822}
1823
1824bool WriteFmtpParameters(const cricket::CodecParameterMap& parameters,
1825 rtc::StringBuilder* os) {
1826 bool empty = true;
1827 const char* delimiter = ""; // No delimiter before first parameter.
1828 for (const auto& entry : parameters) {
1829 const std::string& key = entry.first;
1830 const std::string& value = entry.second;
1831
1832 if (IsFmtpParam(key)) {
1833 *os << delimiter;
1834 // A semicolon before each subsequent parameter.
1835 delimiter = kSdpDelimiterSemicolon;
1836 WriteFmtpParameter(key, value, os);
1837 empty = false;
1838 }
1839 }
1840
1841 return !empty;
1842}
1843
1844template <class T>
1845void AddFmtpLine(const T& codec, std::string* message) {
1846 rtc::StringBuilder os;
1847 WriteFmtpHeader(codec.id, &os);
1848 os << kSdpDelimiterSpace;
1849 // Create FMTP line and check that it's nonempty.
1850 if (WriteFmtpParameters(codec.params, &os)) {
1851 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1852 }
1853 return;
1854}
1855
1856template <class T>
1857void AddPacketizationLine(const T& codec, std::string* message) {
1858 if (!codec.packetization) {
1859 return;
1860 }
1861 rtc::StringBuilder os;
1862 WritePacketizationHeader(codec.id, &os);
1863 os << " " << *codec.packetization;
1864 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1865}
1866
1867template <class T>
1868void AddRtcpFbLines(const T& codec, std::string* message) {
1869 for (const cricket::FeedbackParam& param : codec.feedback_params.params()) {
1870 rtc::StringBuilder os;
1871 WriteRtcpFbHeader(codec.id, &os);
1872 os << " " << param.id();
1873 if (!param.param().empty()) {
1874 os << " " << param.param();
1875 }
1876 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1877 }
1878}
1879
1880bool GetMinValue(const std::vector<int>& values, int* value) {
1881 if (values.empty()) {
1882 return false;
1883 }
1884 auto it = absl::c_min_element(values);
1885 *value = *it;
1886 return true;
1887}
1888
1889bool GetParameter(const std::string& name,
1890 const cricket::CodecParameterMap& params,
1891 int* value) {
1892 std::map<std::string, std::string>::const_iterator found = params.find(name);
1893 if (found == params.end()) {
1894 return false;
1895 }
1896 if (!rtc::FromString(found->second, value)) {
1897 return false;
1898 }
1899 return true;
1900}
1901
1902void BuildRtpMap(const MediaContentDescription* media_desc,
1903 const cricket::MediaType media_type,
1904 std::string* message) {
1905 RTC_DCHECK(message != NULL);
1906 RTC_DCHECK(media_desc != NULL);
1907 rtc::StringBuilder os;
1908 if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
1909 for (const cricket::VideoCodec& codec : media_desc->as_video()->codecs()) {
1910 // RFC 4566
1911 // a=rtpmap:<payload type> <encoding name>/<clock rate>
1912 // [/<encodingparameters>]
1913 if (codec.id != kWildcardPayloadType) {
1914 InitAttrLine(kAttributeRtpmap, &os);
1915 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << codec.id << " " << codec.name << "/"
1916 << cricket::kVideoCodecClockrate;
1917 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1918 }
1919 AddPacketizationLine(codec, message);
1920 AddRtcpFbLines(codec, message);
1921 AddFmtpLine(codec, message);
1922 }
1923 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
1924 std::vector<int> ptimes;
1925 std::vector<int> maxptimes;
1926 int max_minptime = 0;
1927 for (const cricket::AudioCodec& codec : media_desc->as_audio()->codecs()) {
1928 RTC_DCHECK(!codec.name.empty());
1929 // RFC 4566
1930 // a=rtpmap:<payload type> <encoding name>/<clock rate>
1931 // [/<encodingparameters>]
1932 InitAttrLine(kAttributeRtpmap, &os);
1933 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << codec.id << " ";
1934 os << codec.name << "/" << codec.clockrate;
1935 if (codec.channels != 1) {
1936 os << "/" << codec.channels;
1937 }
1938 AddLine(os.str(), message);
1939 AddRtcpFbLines(codec, message);
1940 AddFmtpLine(codec, message);
1941 int minptime = 0;
1942 if (GetParameter(kCodecParamMinPTime, codec.params, &minptime)) {
1943 max_minptime = std::max(minptime, max_minptime);
1944 }
1945 int ptime;
1946 if (GetParameter(kCodecParamPTime, codec.params, &ptime)) {
1947 ptimes.push_back(ptime);
1948 }
1949 int maxptime;
1950 if (GetParameter(kCodecParamMaxPTime, codec.params, &maxptime)) {
1951 maxptimes.push_back(maxptime);
1952 }
1953 }
1954 // Populate the maxptime attribute with the smallest maxptime of all codecs
1955 // under the same m-line.
1956 int min_maxptime = INT_MAX;
1957 if (GetMinValue(maxptimes, &min_maxptime)) {
1958 AddAttributeLine(kCodecParamMaxPTime, min_maxptime, message);
1959 }
1960 RTC_DCHECK(min_maxptime > max_minptime);
1961 // Populate the ptime attribute with the smallest ptime or the largest
1962 // minptime, whichever is the largest, for all codecs under the same m-line.
1963 int ptime = INT_MAX;
1964 if (GetMinValue(ptimes, &ptime)) {
1965 ptime = std::min(ptime, min_maxptime);
1966 ptime = std::max(ptime, max_minptime);
1967 AddAttributeLine(kCodecParamPTime, ptime, message);
1968 }
1969 }
1970}
1971
1972void BuildCandidate(const std::vector<Candidate>& candidates,
1973 bool include_ufrag,
1974 std::string* message) {
1975 rtc::StringBuilder os;
1976
1977 for (const Candidate& candidate : candidates) {
1978 // RFC 5245
1979 // a=candidate:<foundation> <component-id> <transport> <priority>
1980 // <connection-address> <port> typ <candidate-types>
1981 // [raddr <connection-address>] [rport <port>]
1982 // *(SP extension-att-name SP extension-att-value)
1983 std::string type;
1984 // Map the cricket candidate type to "host" / "srflx" / "prflx" / "relay"
1985 if (candidate.type() == cricket::LOCAL_PORT_TYPE) {
1986 type = kCandidateHost;
1987 } else if (candidate.type() == cricket::STUN_PORT_TYPE) {
1988 type = kCandidateSrflx;
1989 } else if (candidate.type() == cricket::RELAY_PORT_TYPE) {
1990 type = kCandidateRelay;
1991 } else if (candidate.type() == cricket::PRFLX_PORT_TYPE) {
1992 type = kCandidatePrflx;
1993 // Peer reflexive candidate may be signaled for being removed.
1994 } else {
1995 RTC_NOTREACHED();
1996 // Never write out candidates if we don't know the type.
1997 continue;
1998 }
1999
2000 InitAttrLine(kAttributeCandidate, &os);
2001 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << candidate.foundation() << " "
2002 << candidate.component() << " " << candidate.protocol() << " "
2003 << candidate.priority() << " "
2004 << (candidate.address().ipaddr().IsNil()
2005 ? candidate.address().hostname()
2006 : candidate.address().ipaddr().ToString())
2007 << " " << candidate.address().PortAsString() << " "
2008 << kAttributeCandidateTyp << " " << type << " ";
2009
2010 // Related address
2011 if (!candidate.related_address().IsNil()) {
2012 os << kAttributeCandidateRaddr << " "
2013 << candidate.related_address().ipaddr().ToString() << " "
2014 << kAttributeCandidateRport << " "
2015 << candidate.related_address().PortAsString() << " ";
2016 }
2017
2018 // Note that we allow the tcptype to be missing, for backwards
2019 // compatibility; the implementation treats this as a passive candidate.
2020 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11466): Treat a missing tcptype as an error?
2021 if (candidate.protocol() == cricket::TCP_PROTOCOL_NAME &&
2022 !candidate.tcptype().empty()) {
2023 os << kTcpCandidateType << " " << candidate.tcptype() << " ";
2024 }
2025
2026 // Extensions
2027 os << kAttributeCandidateGeneration << " " << candidate.generation();
2028 if (include_ufrag && !candidate.username().empty()) {
2029 os << " " << kAttributeCandidateUfrag << " " << candidate.username();
2030 }
2031 if (candidate.network_id() > 0) {
2032 os << " " << kAttributeCandidateNetworkId << " "
2033 << candidate.network_id();
2034 }
2035 if (candidate.network_cost() > 0) {
2036 os << " " << kAttributeCandidateNetworkCost << " "
2037 << candidate.network_cost();
2038 }
2039
2040 AddLine(os.str(), message);
2041 }
2042}
2043
2044void BuildIceOptions(const std::vector<std::string>& transport_options,
2045 std::string* message) {
2046 if (!transport_options.empty()) {
2047 rtc::StringBuilder os;
2048 InitAttrLine(kAttributeIceOption, &os);
2049 os << kSdpDelimiterColon << transport_options[0];
2050 for (size_t i = 1; i < transport_options.size(); ++i) {
2051 os << kSdpDelimiterSpace << transport_options[i];
2052 }
2053 AddLine(os.str(), message);
2054 }
2055}
2056
2057bool ParseConnectionData(const std::string& line,
2058 rtc::SocketAddress* addr,
2059 SdpParseError* error) {
2060 // Parse the line from left to right.
2061 std::string token;
2062 std::string rightpart;
2063 // RFC 4566
2064 // c=<nettype> <addrtype> <connection-address>
2065 // Skip the "c="
2066 if (!rtc::tokenize_first(line, kSdpDelimiterEqualChar, &token, &rightpart)) {
2067 return ParseFailed(line, "Failed to parse the network type.", error);
2068 }
2069
2070 // Extract and verify the <nettype>
2071 if (!rtc::tokenize_first(rightpart, kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &token,
2072 &rightpart) ||
2073 token != kConnectionNettype) {
2074 return ParseFailed(line,
2075 "Failed to parse the connection data. The network type "
2076 "is not currently supported.",
2077 error);
2078 }
2079
2080 // Extract the "<addrtype>" and "<connection-address>".
2081 if (!rtc::tokenize_first(rightpart, kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &token,
2082 &rightpart)) {
2083 return ParseFailed(line, "Failed to parse the address type.", error);
2084 }
2085
2086 // The rightpart part should be the IP address without the slash which is used
2087 // for multicast.
2088 if (rightpart.find('/') != std::string::npos) {
2089 return ParseFailed(line,
2090 "Failed to parse the connection data. Multicast is not "
2091 "currently supported.",
2092 error);
2093 }
2094 addr->SetIP(rightpart);
2095
2096 // Verify that the addrtype matches the type of the parsed address.
2097 if ((addr->family() == AF_INET && token != "IP4") ||
2098 (addr->family() == AF_INET6 && token != "IP6")) {
2099 addr->Clear();
2100 return ParseFailed(
2101 line,
2102 "Failed to parse the connection data. The address type is mismatching.",
2103 error);
2104 }
2105 return true;
2106}
2107
2108bool ParseSessionDescription(const std::string& message,
2109 size_t* pos,
2110 std::string* session_id,
2111 std::string* session_version,
2112 TransportDescription* session_td,
2113 RtpHeaderExtensions* session_extmaps,
2114 rtc::SocketAddress* connection_addr,
2115 cricket::SessionDescription* desc,
2116 SdpParseError* error) {
2117 std::string line;
2118
2119 desc->set_msid_supported(false);
2120 desc->set_extmap_allow_mixed(false);
2121 // RFC 4566
2122 // v= (protocol version)
2123 if (!GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeVersion)) {
2124 return ParseFailedExpectLine(message, *pos, kLineTypeVersion, std::string(),
2125 error);
2126 }
2127 // RFC 4566
2128 // o=<username> <sess-id> <sess-version> <nettype> <addrtype>
2129 // <unicast-address>
2130 if (!GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeOrigin)) {
2131 return ParseFailedExpectLine(message, *pos, kLineTypeOrigin, std::string(),
2132 error);
2133 }
2134 std::vector<std::string> fields;
2135 rtc::split(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength), kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &fields);
2136 const size_t expected_fields = 6;
2137 if (fields.size() != expected_fields) {
2138 return ParseFailedExpectFieldNum(line, expected_fields, error);
2139 }
2140 *session_id = fields[1];
2141 *session_version = fields[2];
2142
2143 // RFC 4566
2144 // s= (session name)
2145 if (!GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeSessionName)) {
2146 return ParseFailedExpectLine(message, *pos, kLineTypeSessionName,
2147 std::string(), error);
2148 }
2149
2150 // absl::optional lines
2151 // Those are the optional lines, so shouldn't return false if not present.
2152 // RFC 4566
2153 // i=* (session information)
2154 GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeSessionInfo);
2155
2156 // RFC 4566
2157 // u=* (URI of description)
2158 GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeSessionUri);
2159
2160 // RFC 4566
2161 // e=* (email address)
2162 GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeSessionEmail);
2163
2164 // RFC 4566
2165 // p=* (phone number)
2166 GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeSessionPhone);
2167
2168 // RFC 4566
2169 // c=* (connection information -- not required if included in
2170 // all media)
2171 if (GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeConnection)) {
2172 if (!ParseConnectionData(line, connection_addr, error)) {
2173 return false;
2174 }
2175 }
2176
2177 // RFC 4566
2178 // b=* (zero or more bandwidth information lines)
2179 while (GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeSessionBandwidth)) {
2180 // By pass zero or more b lines.
2181 }
2182
2183 // RFC 4566
2184 // One or more time descriptions ("t=" and "r=" lines; see below)
2185 // t= (time the session is active)
2186 // r=* (zero or more repeat times)
2187 // Ensure there's at least one time description
2188 if (!GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeTiming)) {
2189 return ParseFailedExpectLine(message, *pos, kLineTypeTiming, std::string(),
2190 error);
2191 }
2192
2193 while (GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeRepeatTimes)) {
2194 // By pass zero or more r lines.
2195 }
2196
2197 // Go through the rest of the time descriptions
2198 while (GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeTiming)) {
2199 while (GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeRepeatTimes)) {
2200 // By pass zero or more r lines.
2201 }
2202 }
2203
2204 // RFC 4566
2205 // z=* (time zone adjustments)
2206 GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeTimeZone);
2207
2208 // RFC 4566
2209 // k=* (encryption key)
2210 GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeEncryptionKey);
2211
2212 // RFC 4566
2213 // a=* (zero or more session attribute lines)
2214 while (GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeAttributes)) {
2215 if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeGroup)) {
2216 if (!ParseGroupAttribute(line, desc, error)) {
2217 return false;
2218 }
2219 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeIceUfrag)) {
2220 if (!GetValue(line, kAttributeIceUfrag, &(session_td->ice_ufrag),
2221 error)) {
2222 return false;
2223 }
2224 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeIcePwd)) {
2225 if (!GetValue(line, kAttributeIcePwd, &(session_td->ice_pwd), error)) {
2226 return false;
2227 }
2228 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeIceLite)) {
2229 session_td->ice_mode = cricket::ICEMODE_LITE;
2230 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeIceOption)) {
2231 if (!ParseIceOptions(line, &(session_td->transport_options), error)) {
2232 return false;
2233 }
2234 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeFingerprint)) {
2235 if (session_td->identity_fingerprint.get()) {
2236 return ParseFailed(
2237 line,
2238 "Can't have multiple fingerprint attributes at the same level.",
2239 error);
2240 }
2241 std::unique_ptr<rtc::SSLFingerprint> fingerprint;
2242 if (!ParseFingerprintAttribute(line, &fingerprint, error)) {
2243 return false;
2244 }
2245 session_td->identity_fingerprint = std::move(fingerprint);
2246 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeSetup)) {
2247 if (!ParseDtlsSetup(line, &(session_td->connection_role), error)) {
2248 return false;
2249 }
2250 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeMsidSemantics)) {
2251 std::string semantics;
2252 if (!GetValue(line, kAttributeMsidSemantics, &semantics, error)) {
2253 return false;
2254 }
2255 desc->set_msid_supported(
2256 CaseInsensitiveFind(semantics, kMediaStreamSemantic));
2257 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeExtmapAllowMixed)) {
2258 desc->set_extmap_allow_mixed(true);
2259 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeExtmap)) {
2260 RtpExtension extmap;
2261 if (!ParseExtmap(line, &extmap, error)) {
2262 return false;
2263 }
2264 session_extmaps->push_back(extmap);
2265 }
2266 }
2267
2268 return true;
2269}
2270
2271bool ParseGroupAttribute(const std::string& line,
2272 cricket::SessionDescription* desc,
2273 SdpParseError* error) {
2274 RTC_DCHECK(desc != NULL);
2275
2276 // RFC 5888 and draft-holmberg-mmusic-sdp-bundle-negotiation-00
2277 // a=group:BUNDLE video voice
2278 std::vector<std::string> fields;
2279 rtc::split(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength), kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &fields);
2280 std::string semantics;
2281 if (!GetValue(fields[0], kAttributeGroup, &semantics, error)) {
2282 return false;
2283 }
2284 cricket::ContentGroup group(semantics);
2285 for (size_t i = 1; i < fields.size(); ++i) {
2286 group.AddContentName(fields[i]);
2287 }
2288 desc->AddGroup(group);
2289 return true;
2290}
2291
2292static bool ParseFingerprintAttribute(
2293 const std::string& line,
2294 std::unique_ptr<rtc::SSLFingerprint>* fingerprint,
2295 SdpParseError* error) {
2296 std::vector<std::string> fields;
2297 rtc::split(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength), kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &fields);
2298 const size_t expected_fields = 2;
2299 if (fields.size() != expected_fields) {
2300 return ParseFailedExpectFieldNum(line, expected_fields, error);
2301 }
2302
2303 // The first field here is "fingerprint:<hash>.
2304 std::string algorithm;
2305 if (!GetValue(fields[0], kAttributeFingerprint, &algorithm, error)) {
2306 return false;
2307 }
2308
2309 // Downcase the algorithm. Note that we don't need to downcase the
2310 // fingerprint because hex_decode can handle upper-case.
2311 absl::c_transform(algorithm, algorithm.begin(), ::tolower);
2312
2313 // The second field is the digest value. De-hexify it.
2314 *fingerprint =
2315 rtc::SSLFingerprint::CreateUniqueFromRfc4572(algorithm, fields[1]);
2316 if (!*fingerprint) {
2317 return ParseFailed(line, "Failed to create fingerprint from the digest.",
2318 error);
2319 }
2320
2321 return true;
2322}
2323
2324static bool ParseDtlsSetup(const std::string& line,
2325 cricket::ConnectionRole* role,
2326 SdpParseError* error) {
2327 // setup-attr = "a=setup:" role
2328 // role = "active" / "passive" / "actpass" / "holdconn"
2329 std::vector<std::string> fields;
2330 rtc::split(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength), kSdpDelimiterColonChar, &fields);
2331 const size_t expected_fields = 2;
2332 if (fields.size() != expected_fields) {
2333 return ParseFailedExpectFieldNum(line, expected_fields, error);
2334 }
2335 std::string role_str = fields[1];
2336 if (!cricket::StringToConnectionRole(role_str, role)) {
2337 return ParseFailed(line, "Invalid attribute value.", error);
2338 }
2339 return true;
2340}
2341
2342static bool ParseMsidAttribute(const std::string& line,
2343 std::vector<std::string>* stream_ids,
2344 std::string* track_id,
2345 SdpParseError* error) {
2346 // https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-mmusic-msid/16/
2347 // a=msid:<stream id> <track id>
2348 // msid-value = msid-id [ SP msid-appdata ]
2349 // msid-id = 1*64token-char ; see RFC 4566
2350 // msid-appdata = 1*64token-char ; see RFC 4566
2351 std::string field1;
2352 std::string new_stream_id;
2353 std::string new_track_id;
2354 if (!rtc::tokenize_first(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength),
2355 kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &field1, &new_track_id)) {
2356 const size_t expected_fields = 2;
2357 return ParseFailedExpectFieldNum(line, expected_fields, error);
2358 }
2359
2360 if (new_track_id.empty()) {
2361 return ParseFailed(line, "Missing track ID in msid attribute.", error);
2362 }
2363 // All track ids should be the same within an m section in a Unified Plan SDP.
2364 if (!track_id->empty() && new_track_id.compare(*track_id) != 0) {
2365 return ParseFailed(
2366 line, "Two different track IDs in msid attribute in one m= section",
2367 error);
2368 }
2369 *track_id = new_track_id;
2370
2371 // msid:<msid-id>
2372 if (!GetValue(field1, kAttributeMsid, &new_stream_id, error)) {
2373 return false;
2374 }
2375 if (new_stream_id.empty()) {
2376 return ParseFailed(line, "Missing stream ID in msid attribute.", error);
2377 }
2378 // The special value "-" indicates "no MediaStream".
2379 if (new_stream_id.compare(kNoStreamMsid) != 0) {
2380 stream_ids->push_back(new_stream_id);
2381 }
2382 return true;
2383}
2384
2385static void RemoveInvalidRidDescriptions(const std::vector<int>& payload_types,
2386 std::vector<RidDescription>* rids) {
2387 RTC_DCHECK(rids);
2388 std::set<std::string> to_remove;
2389 std::set<std::string> unique_rids;
2390
2391 // Check the rids to see which ones should be removed.
2392 for (RidDescription& rid : *rids) {
2393 // In the case of a duplicate, the entire "a=rid" line, and all "a=rid"
2394 // lines with rid-ids that duplicate this line, are discarded and MUST NOT
2395 // be included in the SDP Answer.
2396 auto pair = unique_rids.insert(rid.rid);
2397 // Insert will "fail" if element already exists.
2398 if (!pair.second) {
2399 to_remove.insert(rid.rid);
2400 continue;
2401 }
2402
2403 // If the "a=rid" line contains a "pt=", the list of payload types
2404 // is verified against the list of valid payload types for the media
2405 // section (that is, those listed on the "m=" line). Any PT missing
2406 // from the "m=" line is discarded from the set of values in the
2407 // "pt=". If no values are left in the "pt=" parameter after this
2408 // processing, then the "a=rid" line is discarded.
2409 if (rid.payload_types.empty()) {
2410 // If formats were not specified, rid should not be removed.
2411 continue;
2412 }
2413
2414 // Note: Spec does not mention how to handle duplicate formats.
2415 // Media section does not handle duplicates either.
2416 std::set<int> removed_formats;
2417 for (int payload_type : rid.payload_types) {
2418 if (!absl::c_linear_search(payload_types, payload_type)) {
2419 removed_formats.insert(payload_type);
2420 }
2421 }
2422
2423 rid.payload_types.erase(
2424 std::remove_if(rid.payload_types.begin(), rid.payload_types.end(),
2425 [&removed_formats](int format) {
2426 return removed_formats.count(format) > 0;
2427 }),
2428 rid.payload_types.end());
2429
2430 // If all formats were removed then remove the rid alogether.
2431 if (rid.payload_types.empty()) {
2432 to_remove.insert(rid.rid);
2433 }
2434 }
2435
2436 // Remove every rid description that appears in the to_remove list.
2437 if (!to_remove.empty()) {
2438 rids->erase(std::remove_if(rids->begin(), rids->end(),
2439 [&to_remove](const RidDescription& rid) {
2440 return to_remove.count(rid.rid) > 0;
2441 }),
2442 rids->end());
2443 }
2444}
2445
2446// Create a new list (because SimulcastLayerList is immutable) without any
2447// layers that have a rid in the to_remove list.
2448// If a group of alternatives is empty after removing layers, the group should
2449// be removed altogether.
2450static SimulcastLayerList RemoveRidsFromSimulcastLayerList(
2451 const std::set<std::string>& to_remove,
2452 const SimulcastLayerList& layers) {
2453 SimulcastLayerList result;
2454 for (const std::vector<SimulcastLayer>& vector : layers) {
2455 std::vector<SimulcastLayer> new_layers;
2456 for (const SimulcastLayer& layer : vector) {
2457 if (to_remove.find(layer.rid) == to_remove.end()) {
2458 new_layers.push_back(layer);
2459 }
2460 }
2461 // If all layers were removed, do not add an entry.
2462 if (!new_layers.empty()) {
2463 result.AddLayerWithAlternatives(new_layers);
2464 }
2465 }
2466
2467 return result;
2468}
2469
2470// Will remove Simulcast Layers if:
2471// 1. They appear in both send and receive directions.
2472// 2. They do not appear in the list of |valid_rids|.
2473static void RemoveInvalidRidsFromSimulcast(
2474 const std::vector<RidDescription>& valid_rids,
2475 SimulcastDescription* simulcast) {
2476 RTC_DCHECK(simulcast);
2477 std::set<std::string> to_remove;
2478 std::vector<SimulcastLayer> all_send_layers =
2479 simulcast->send_layers().GetAllLayers();
2480 std::vector<SimulcastLayer> all_receive_layers =
2481 simulcast->receive_layers().GetAllLayers();
2482
2483 // If a rid appears in both send and receive directions, remove it from both.
2484 // This algorithm runs in O(n^2) time, but for small n (as is the case with
2485 // simulcast layers) it should still perform well.
2486 for (const SimulcastLayer& send_layer : all_send_layers) {
2487 if (absl::c_any_of(all_receive_layers,
2488 [&send_layer](const SimulcastLayer& layer) {
2489 return layer.rid == send_layer.rid;
2490 })) {
2491 to_remove.insert(send_layer.rid);
2492 }
2493 }
2494
2495 // Add any rid that is not in the valid list to the remove set.
2496 for (const SimulcastLayer& send_layer : all_send_layers) {
2497 if (absl::c_none_of(valid_rids, [&send_layer](const RidDescription& rid) {
2498 return send_layer.rid == rid.rid &&
2499 rid.direction == cricket::RidDirection::kSend;
2500 })) {
2501 to_remove.insert(send_layer.rid);
2502 }
2503 }
2504
2505 // Add any rid that is not in the valid list to the remove set.
2506 for (const SimulcastLayer& receive_layer : all_receive_layers) {
2507 if (absl::c_none_of(
2508 valid_rids, [&receive_layer](const RidDescription& rid) {
2509 return receive_layer.rid == rid.rid &&
2510 rid.direction == cricket::RidDirection::kReceive;
2511 })) {
2512 to_remove.insert(receive_layer.rid);
2513 }
2514 }
2515
2516 simulcast->send_layers() =
2517 RemoveRidsFromSimulcastLayerList(to_remove, simulcast->send_layers());
2518 simulcast->receive_layers() =
2519 RemoveRidsFromSimulcastLayerList(to_remove, simulcast->receive_layers());
2520}
