2522// RFC 3551
2523// PT encoding media type clock rate channels
2524// name (Hz)
2525// 0 PCMU A 8,000 1
2526// 1 reserved A
2527// 2 reserved A
2528// 3 GSM A 8,000 1
2529// 4 G723 A 8,000 1
2530// 5 DVI4 A 8,000 1
2531// 6 DVI4 A 16,000 1
2532// 7 LPC A 8,000 1
2533// 8 PCMA A 8,000 1
2534// 9 G722 A 8,000 1
2535// 10 L16 A 44,100 2
2536// 11 L16 A 44,100 1
2537// 12 QCELP A 8,000 1
2538// 13 CN A 8,000 1
2539// 14 MPA A 90,000 (see text)
2540// 15 G728 A 8,000 1
2541// 16 DVI4 A 11,025 1
2542// 17 DVI4 A 22,050 1
2543// 18 G729 A 8,000 1
2544struct StaticPayloadAudioCodec {
2545 const char* name;
2546 int clockrate;
2547 size_t channels;
2548};
2549static const StaticPayloadAudioCodec kStaticPayloadAudioCodecs[] = {
2550 {"PCMU", 8000, 1}, {"reserved", 0, 0}, {"reserved", 0, 0},
2551 {"GSM", 8000, 1}, {"G723", 8000, 1}, {"DVI4", 8000, 1},
2552 {"DVI4", 16000, 1}, {"LPC", 8000, 1}, {"PCMA", 8000, 1},
2553 {"G722", 8000, 1}, {"L16", 44100, 2}, {"L16", 44100, 1},
2554 {"QCELP", 8000, 1}, {"CN", 8000, 1}, {"MPA", 90000, 1},
2555 {"G728", 8000, 1}, {"DVI4", 11025, 1}, {"DVI4", 22050, 1},
2556 {"G729", 8000, 1},
2557};
2558
2559void MaybeCreateStaticPayloadAudioCodecs(const std::vector<int>& fmts,
2560 AudioContentDescription* media_desc) {
2561 if (!media_desc) {
2562 return;
2563 }
2564 RTC_DCHECK(media_desc->codecs().empty());
2565 for (int payload_type : fmts) {
2566 if (!media_desc->HasCodec(payload_type) && payload_type >= 0 &&
2567 static_cast<uint32_t>(payload_type) <
2568 arraysize(kStaticPayloadAudioCodecs)) {
2569 std::string encoding_name = kStaticPayloadAudioCodecs[payload_type].name;
2570 int clock_rate = kStaticPayloadAudioCodecs[payload_type].clockrate;
2571 size_t channels = kStaticPayloadAudioCodecs[payload_type].channels;
2572 media_desc->AddCodec(cricket::AudioCodec(payload_type, encoding_name,
2573 clock_rate, 0, channels));
2574 }
2575 }
2576}
2577
2578template <class C>
2579static std::unique_ptr<C> ParseContentDescription(
2580 const std::string& message,
2581 const cricket::MediaType media_type,
2582 int mline_index,
2583 const std::string& protocol,
2584 const std::vector<int>& payload_types,
2585 size_t* pos,
2586 std::string* content_name,
2587 bool* bundle_only,
2588 int* msid_signaling,
2589 TransportDescription* transport,
2590 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<JsepIceCandidate>>* candidates,
2591 webrtc::SdpParseError* error) {
2592 auto media_desc = std::make_unique<C>();
2593 media_desc->set_extmap_allow_mixed_enum(MediaContentDescription::kNo);
2594 if (!ParseContent(message, media_type, mline_index, protocol, payload_types,
2595 pos, content_name, bundle_only, msid_signaling,
2596 media_desc.get(), transport, candidates, error)) {
2597 return nullptr;
2598 }
2599 // Sort the codecs according to the m-line fmt list.
2600 std::unordered_map<int, int> payload_type_preferences;
2601 // "size + 1" so that the lowest preference payload type has a preference of
2602 // 1, which is greater than the default (0) for payload types not in the fmt
2603 // list.
2604 int preference = static_cast<int>(payload_types.size() + 1);
2605 for (int pt : payload_types) {
2606 payload_type_preferences[pt] = preference--;
2607 }
2608 std::vector<typename C::CodecType> codecs = media_desc->codecs();
2609 absl::c_sort(
2610 codecs, [&payload_type_preferences](const typename C::CodecType& a,
2611 const typename C::CodecType& b) {
2612 return payload_type_preferences[a.id] > payload_type_preferences[b.id];
2613 });
2614 media_desc->set_codecs(codecs);
2615 return media_desc;
2616}
2617
2618bool ParseMediaDescription(
2619 const std::string& message,
2620 const TransportDescription& session_td,
2621 const RtpHeaderExtensions& session_extmaps,
2622 size_t* pos,
2623 const rtc::SocketAddress& session_connection_addr,
2624 cricket::SessionDescription* desc,
2625 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<JsepIceCandidate>>* candidates,
2626 SdpParseError* error) {
2627 RTC_DCHECK(desc != NULL);
2628 std::string line;
2629 int mline_index = -1;
2630 int msid_signaling = 0;
2631
2632 // Zero or more media descriptions
2633 // RFC 4566
2634 // m=<media> <port> <proto> <fmt>
2635 while (GetLineWithType(message, pos, &line, kLineTypeMedia)) {
2636 ++mline_index;
2637
2638 std::vector<std::string> fields;
2639 rtc::split(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength), kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &fields);
2640
2641 const size_t expected_min_fields = 4;
2642 if (fields.size() < expected_min_fields) {
2643 return ParseFailedExpectMinFieldNum(line, expected_min_fields, error);
2644 }
2645 bool port_rejected = false;
2646 // RFC 3264
2647 // To reject an offered stream, the port number in the corresponding stream
2648 // in the answer MUST be set to zero.
2649 if (fields[1] == kMediaPortRejected) {
2650 port_rejected = true;
2651 }
2652
2653 int port = 0;
2654 if (!rtc::FromString<int>(fields[1], &port) || !IsValidPort(port)) {
2655 return ParseFailed(line, "The port number is invalid", error);
2656 }
2657 const std::string& protocol = fields[2];
2658
2659 // <fmt>
2660 std::vector<int> payload_types;
2661 if (cricket::IsRtpProtocol(protocol)) {
2662 for (size_t j = 3; j < fields.size(); ++j) {
2663 int pl = 0;
2664 if (!GetPayloadTypeFromString(line, fields[j], &pl, error)) {
2665 return false;
2666 }
2667 payload_types.push_back(pl);
2668 }
2669 }
2670
2671 // Make a temporary TransportDescription based on |session_td|.
2672 // Some of this gets overwritten by ParseContent.
2673 TransportDescription transport(
2674 session_td.transport_options, session_td.ice_ufrag, session_td.ice_pwd,
2675 session_td.ice_mode, session_td.connection_role,
2676 session_td.identity_fingerprint.get());
2677
2678 std::unique_ptr<MediaContentDescription> content;
2679 std::string content_name;
2680 bool bundle_only = false;
2681 int section_msid_signaling = 0;
2682 const std::string& media_type = fields[0];
2683 if ((media_type == kMediaTypeVideo || media_type == kMediaTypeAudio) &&
2684 !cricket::IsRtpProtocol(protocol)) {
2685 return ParseFailed(line, "Unsupported protocol for media type", error);
2686 }
2687 if (media_type == kMediaTypeVideo) {
2688 content = ParseContentDescription<VideoContentDescription>(
2689 message, cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO, mline_index, protocol,
2690 payload_types, pos, &content_name, &bundle_only,
2691 &section_msid_signaling, &transport, candidates, error);
2692 } else if (media_type == kMediaTypeAudio) {
2693 content = ParseContentDescription<AudioContentDescription>(
2694 message, cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO, mline_index, protocol,
2695 payload_types, pos, &content_name, &bundle_only,
2696 &section_msid_signaling, &transport, candidates, error);
2697 } else if (media_type == kMediaTypeData) {
2698 if (cricket::IsDtlsSctp(protocol)) {
2699 // The draft-03 format is:
2700 // m=application <port> DTLS/SCTP <sctp-port>...
2701 // use_sctpmap should be false.
2702 // The draft-26 format is:
2703 // m=application <port> UDP/DTLS/SCTP webrtc-datachannel
2704 // use_sctpmap should be false.
2705 auto data_desc = std::make_unique<SctpDataContentDescription>();
2706 // Default max message size is 64K
2707 // according to draft-ietf-mmusic-sctp-sdp-26
2708 data_desc->set_max_message_size(kDefaultSctpMaxMessageSize);
2709 int p;
2710 if (rtc::FromString(fields[3], &p)) {
2711 data_desc->set_port(p);
2712 } else if (fields[3] == kDefaultSctpmapProtocol) {
2713 data_desc->set_use_sctpmap(false);
2714 }
2715 if (!ParseContent(message, cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_DATA, mline_index,
2716 protocol, payload_types, pos, &content_name,
2717 &bundle_only, &section_msid_signaling,
2718 data_desc.get(), &transport, candidates, error)) {
2719 return false;
2720 }
2721 data_desc->set_protocol(protocol);
2722 content = std::move(data_desc);
2723 } else {
2724 return ParseFailed(line, "Unsupported protocol for media type", error);
2725 }
2726 } else {
2727 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unsupported media type: " << line;
2728 auto unsupported_desc =
2729 std::make_unique<UnsupportedContentDescription>(media_type);
2730 if (!ParseContent(message, cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_UNSUPPORTED, mline_index,
2731 protocol, payload_types, pos, &content_name,
2732 &bundle_only, &section_msid_signaling,
2733 unsupported_desc.get(), &transport, candidates,
2734 error)) {
2735 return false;
2736 }
2737 unsupported_desc->set_protocol(protocol);
2738 content = std::move(unsupported_desc);
2739 }
2740 if (!content.get()) {
2741 // ParseContentDescription returns NULL if failed.
2742 return false;
2743 }
2744
2745 msid_signaling |= section_msid_signaling;
2746
2747 bool content_rejected = false;
2748 // A port of 0 is not interpreted as a rejected m= section when it's
2749 // used along with a=bundle-only.
2750 if (bundle_only) {
2751 if (!port_rejected) {
2752 // Usage of bundle-only with a nonzero port is unspecified. So just
2753 // ignore bundle-only if we see this.
2754 bundle_only = false;
2755 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
2756 << "a=bundle-only attribute observed with a nonzero "
2757 "port; this usage is unspecified so the attribute is being "
2758 "ignored.";
2759 }
2760 } else {
2761 // If not using bundle-only, interpret port 0 in the normal way; the m=
2762 // section is being rejected.
2763 content_rejected = port_rejected;
2764 }
2765
2766 if (content->as_unsupported()) {
2767 content_rejected = true;
2768 } else if (cricket::IsRtpProtocol(protocol) && !content->as_sctp()) {
2769 content->set_protocol(protocol);
2770 // Set the extmap.
2771 if (!session_extmaps.empty() &&
2772 !content->rtp_header_extensions().empty()) {
2773 return ParseFailed("",
2774 "The a=extmap MUST be either all session level or "
2775 "all media level.",
2776 error);
2777 }
2778 for (size_t i = 0; i < session_extmaps.size(); ++i) {
2779 content->AddRtpHeaderExtension(session_extmaps[i]);
2780 }
2781 } else if (content->as_sctp()) {
2782 // Do nothing, it's OK
2783 } else {
2784 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Parse failed with unknown protocol " << protocol;
2785 return false;
2786 }
2787
2788 // Use the session level connection address if the media level addresses are
2789 // not specified.
2790 rtc::SocketAddress address;
2791 address = content->connection_address().IsNil()
2792 ? session_connection_addr
2793 : content->connection_address();
2794 address.SetPort(port);
2795 content->set_connection_address(address);
2796
2797 desc->AddContent(content_name,
2798 cricket::IsDtlsSctp(protocol) ? MediaProtocolType::kSctp
2799 : MediaProtocolType::kRtp,
2800 content_rejected, bundle_only, std::move(content));
2801 // Create TransportInfo with the media level "ice-pwd" and "ice-ufrag".
2802 desc->AddTransportInfo(TransportInfo(content_name, transport));
2803 }
2804
2805 desc->set_msid_signaling(msid_signaling);
2806
2807 size_t end_of_message = message.size();
2808 if (mline_index == -1 && *pos != end_of_message) {
2809 ParseFailed(message, *pos, "Expects m line.", error);
2810 return false;
2811 }
2812 return true;
2813}

2816 // Codec has not been populated correctly unless the name has been set. This
2817 // can happen if an SDP has an fmtp or rtcp-fb with a payload type but doesn't
2818 // have a corresponding "rtpmap" line.
2819 return !codec.name.empty();

2851// Gets the current codec setting associated with |payload_type|. If there
2852// is no Codec associated with that payload type it returns an empty codec
2853// with that payload type.
2854template <class T>
2855T GetCodecWithPayloadType(const std::vector<T>& codecs, int payload_type) {
2856 const T* codec = FindCodecById(codecs, payload_type);
2857 if (codec)
2858 return *codec;
2859 // Return empty codec with |payload_type|.
2860 T ret_val;
2861 ret_val.id = payload_type;
2862 return ret_val;
2863}
2864
2865// Updates or creates a new codec entry in the audio description.
2866template <class T, class U>
2867void AddOrReplaceCodec(MediaContentDescription* content_desc, const U& codec) {
2868 T* desc = static_cast<T*>(content_desc);
2869 std::vector<U> codecs = desc->codecs();
2870 bool found = false;
2871 for (U& existing_codec : codecs) {
2872 if (codec.id == existing_codec.id) {
2873 // Overwrite existing codec with the new codec.
2874 existing_codec = codec;
2875 found = true;
2876 break;
2877 }
2878 }
2879 if (!found) {
2880 desc->AddCodec(codec);
2881 return;
2882 }
2883 desc->set_codecs(codecs);
2884}
2885
2886// Adds or updates existing codec corresponding to |payload_type| according
2887// to |parameters|.
2888template <class T, class U>
2889void UpdateCodec(MediaContentDescription* content_desc,
2890 int payload_type,
2891 const cricket::CodecParameterMap& parameters) {
2892 // Codec might already have been populated (from rtpmap).
2893 U new_codec = GetCodecWithPayloadType(static_cast<T*>(content_desc)->codecs(),
2894 payload_type);
2895 AddParameters(parameters, &new_codec);
2896 AddOrReplaceCodec<T, U>(content_desc, new_codec);
2897}
2898
2899// Adds or updates existing codec corresponding to |payload_type| according
2900// to |feedback_param|.
2901template <class T, class U>
2902void UpdateCodec(MediaContentDescription* content_desc,
2903 int payload_type,
2904 const cricket::FeedbackParam& feedback_param) {
2905 // Codec might already have been populated (from rtpmap).
2906 U new_codec = GetCodecWithPayloadType(static_cast<T*>(content_desc)->codecs(),
2907 payload_type);
2908 AddFeedbackParameter(feedback_param, &new_codec);
2909 AddOrReplaceCodec<T, U>(content_desc, new_codec);
2910}

2912// Adds or updates existing video codec corresponding to |payload_type|
2913// according to |packetization|.
2914void UpdateVideoCodecPacketization(VideoContentDescription* video_desc,
2915 int payload_type,
2916 const std::string& packetization) {
2917 if (packetization != cricket::kPacketizationParamRaw) {
2918 // Ignore unsupported packetization attribute.
2919 return;
2920 }
2921
2922 // Codec might already have been populated (from rtpmap).
2923 cricket::VideoCodec codec =
2924 GetCodecWithPayloadType(video_desc->codecs(), payload_type);
2925 codec.packetization = packetization;
2926 AddOrReplaceCodec<VideoContentDescription, cricket::VideoCodec>(video_desc,
2927 codec);
2928}

2930template <class T>
2931bool PopWildcardCodec(std::vector<T>* codecs, T* wildcard_codec) {
2932 for (auto iter = codecs->begin(); iter != codecs->end(); ++iter) {
2933 if (iter->id == kWildcardPayloadType) {
2934 *wildcard_codec = *iter;
2935 codecs->erase(iter);
2936 return true;
2937 }
2938 }
2939 return false;
2940}
2941
2942template <class T>
2943void UpdateFromWildcardCodecs(cricket::MediaContentDescriptionImpl<T>* desc) {
2944 auto codecs = desc->codecs();
2945 T wildcard_codec;
2946 if (!PopWildcardCodec(&codecs, &wildcard_codec)) {
2947 return;
2948 }
2949 for (auto& codec : codecs) {
2950 AddFeedbackParameters(wildcard_codec.feedback_params, &codec);
2951 }
2952 desc->set_codecs(codecs);
2953}

2967
2968bool ParseContent(const std::string& message,
2969 const cricket::MediaType media_type,
2970 int mline_index,
2971 const std::string& protocol,
2972 const std::vector<int>& payload_types,
2973 size_t* pos,
2974 std::string* content_name,
2975 bool* bundle_only,
2976 int* msid_signaling,
2977 MediaContentDescription* media_desc,
2978 TransportDescription* transport,
2979 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<JsepIceCandidate>>* candidates,
2980 SdpParseError* error) {
2981 RTC_DCHECK(media_desc != NULL);
2982 RTC_DCHECK(content_name != NULL);
2983 RTC_DCHECK(transport != NULL);
2984
2985 if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
2986 MaybeCreateStaticPayloadAudioCodecs(payload_types, media_desc->as_audio());
2987 }
2988
2989 // The media level "ice-ufrag" and "ice-pwd".
2990 // The candidates before update the media level "ice-pwd" and "ice-ufrag".
2991 Candidates candidates_orig;
2992 std::string line;
2993 std::string mline_id;
2994 // Tracks created out of the ssrc attributes.
2995 StreamParamsVec tracks;
2996 SsrcInfoVec ssrc_infos;
2997 SsrcGroupVec ssrc_groups;
2998 std::string maxptime_as_string;
2999 std::string ptime_as_string;
3000 std::vector<std::string> stream_ids;
3001 std::string track_id;
3002 SdpSerializer deserializer;
3003 std::vector<RidDescription> rids;
3004 SimulcastDescription simulcast;
3005
3006 // Loop until the next m line
3007 while (!IsLineType(message, kLineTypeMedia, *pos)) {
3008 if (!GetLine(message, pos, &line)) {
3009 if (*pos >= message.size()) {
3010 break; // Done parsing
3011 } else {
3012 return ParseFailed(message, *pos, "Invalid SDP line.", error);
3013 }
3014 }
3015
3016 // RFC 4566
3017 // b=* (zero or more bandwidth information lines)
3018 if (IsLineType(line, kLineTypeSessionBandwidth)) {
3019 std::string bandwidth;
3020 std::string bandwidth_type;
3021 if (!rtc::tokenize_first(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength),
3022 kSdpDelimiterColonChar, &bandwidth_type,
3023 &bandwidth)) {
3024 return ParseFailed(
3025 line,
3026 "b= syntax error, does not match b=<modifier>:<bandwidth-value>.",
3027 error);
3028 }
3029 if (!(bandwidth_type == kApplicationSpecificBandwidth ||
3030 bandwidth_type == kTransportSpecificBandwidth)) {
3031 // Ignore unknown bandwidth types.
3032 continue;
3033 }
3034 int b = 0;
3035 if (!GetValueFromString(line, bandwidth, &b, error)) {
3036 return false;
3037 }
3038 // TODO(deadbeef): Historically, applications may be setting a value
3039 // of -1 to mean "unset any previously set bandwidth limit", even
3040 // though ommitting the "b=AS" entirely will do just that. Once we've
3041 // transitioned applications to doing the right thing, it would be
3042 // better to treat this as a hard error instead of just ignoring it.
3043 if (bandwidth_type == kApplicationSpecificBandwidth && b == -1) {
3044 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Ignoring \"b=AS:-1\"; will be treated as \"no "
3045 "bandwidth limit\".";
3046 continue;
3047 }
3048 if (b < 0) {
3049 return ParseFailed(
3050 line, "b=" + bandwidth_type + " value can't be negative.", error);
3051 }
3052 // Convert values. Prevent integer overflow.
3053 if (bandwidth_type == kApplicationSpecificBandwidth) {
3054 b = std::min(b, INT_MAX / 1000) * 1000;
3055 } else {
3056 b = std::min(b, INT_MAX);
3057 }
3058 media_desc->set_bandwidth(b);
3059 media_desc->set_bandwidth_type(bandwidth_type);
3060 continue;
3061 }
3062
3063 // Parse the media level connection data.
3064 if (IsLineType(line, kLineTypeConnection)) {
3065 rtc::SocketAddress addr;
3066 if (!ParseConnectionData(line, &addr, error)) {
3067 return false;
3068 }
3069 media_desc->set_connection_address(addr);
3070 continue;
3071 }
3072
3073 if (!IsLineType(line, kLineTypeAttributes)) {
3074 // TODO(deadbeef): Handle other lines if needed.
3075 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "Ignored line: " << line;
3076 continue;
3077 }
3078
3079 // Handle attributes common to SCTP and RTP.
3080 if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeMid)) {
3081 // RFC 3388
3082 // mid-attribute = "a=mid:" identification-tag
3083 // identification-tag = token
3084 // Use the mid identification-tag as the content name.
3085 if (!GetSingleTokenValue(line, kAttributeMid, &mline_id, error)) {
3086 return false;
3087 }
3088 *content_name = mline_id;
3089 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeBundleOnly)) {
3090 *bundle_only = true;
3091 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeCandidate)) {
3092 Candidate candidate;
3093 if (!ParseCandidate(line, &candidate, error, false)) {
3094 return false;
3095 }
3096 // ParseCandidate will parse non-standard ufrag and password attributes,
3097 // since it's used for candidate trickling, but we only want to process
3098 // the "a=ice-ufrag"/"a=ice-pwd" values in a session description, so
3099 // strip them off at this point.
3100 candidate.set_username(std::string());
3101 candidate.set_password(std::string());
3102 candidates_orig.push_back(candidate);
3103 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeIceUfrag)) {
3104 if (!GetValue(line, kAttributeIceUfrag, &transport->ice_ufrag, error)) {
3105 return false;
3106 }
3107 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeIcePwd)) {
3108 if (!GetValue(line, kAttributeIcePwd, &transport->ice_pwd, error)) {
3109 return false;
3110 }
3111 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeIceOption)) {
3112 if (!ParseIceOptions(line, &transport->transport_options, error)) {
3113 return false;
3114 }
3115 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeFmtp)) {
3116 if (!ParseFmtpAttributes(line, media_type, media_desc, error)) {
3117 return false;
3118 }
3119 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeFingerprint)) {
3120 std::unique_ptr<rtc::SSLFingerprint> fingerprint;
3121 if (!ParseFingerprintAttribute(line, &fingerprint, error)) {
3122 return false;
3123 }
3124 transport->identity_fingerprint = std::move(fingerprint);
3125 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeSetup)) {
3126 if (!ParseDtlsSetup(line, &(transport->connection_role), error)) {
3127 return false;
3128 }
3129 } else if (cricket::IsDtlsSctp(protocol) &&
3130 media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_DATA) {
3131 //
3132 // SCTP specific attributes
3133 //
3134 if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeSctpPort)) {
3135 if (media_desc->as_sctp()->use_sctpmap()) {
3136 return ParseFailed(
3137 line, "sctp-port attribute can't be used with sctpmap.", error);
3138 }
3139 int sctp_port;
3140 if (!ParseSctpPort(line, &sctp_port, error)) {
3141 return false;
3142 }
3143 media_desc->as_sctp()->set_port(sctp_port);
3144 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeMaxMessageSize)) {
3145 int max_message_size;
3146 if (!ParseSctpMaxMessageSize(line, &max_message_size, error)) {
3147 return false;
3148 }
3149 media_desc->as_sctp()->set_max_message_size(max_message_size);
3150 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeSctpmap)) {
3151 // Ignore a=sctpmap: from early versions of draft-ietf-mmusic-sctp-sdp
3152 continue;
3153 }
3154 } else if (cricket::IsRtpProtocol(protocol)) {
3155 //
3156 // RTP specific attributes
3157 //
3158 if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeRtcpMux)) {
3159 media_desc->set_rtcp_mux(true);
3160 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeRtcpReducedSize)) {
3161 media_desc->set_rtcp_reduced_size(true);
3162 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeRtcpRemoteEstimate)) {
3163 media_desc->set_remote_estimate(true);
3164 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeSsrcGroup)) {
3165 if (!ParseSsrcGroupAttribute(line, &ssrc_groups, error)) {
3166 return false;
3167 }
3168 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeSsrc)) {
3169 if (!ParseSsrcAttribute(line, &ssrc_infos, msid_signaling, error)) {
3170 return false;
3171 }
3172 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeCrypto)) {
3173 if (!ParseCryptoAttribute(line, media_desc, error)) {
3174 return false;
3175 }
3176 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeRtpmap)) {
3177 if (!ParseRtpmapAttribute(line, media_type, payload_types, media_desc,
3178 error)) {
3179 return false;
3180 }
3181 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kCodecParamMaxPTime)) {
3182 if (!GetValue(line, kCodecParamMaxPTime, &maxptime_as_string, error)) {
3183 return false;
3184 }
3185 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributePacketization)) {
3186 if (!ParsePacketizationAttribute(line, media_type, media_desc, error)) {
3187 return false;
3188 }
3189 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeRtcpFb)) {
3190 if (!ParseRtcpFbAttribute(line, media_type, media_desc, error)) {
3191 return false;
3192 }
3193 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kCodecParamPTime)) {
3194 if (!GetValue(line, kCodecParamPTime, &ptime_as_string, error)) {
3195 return false;
3196 }
3197 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeSendOnly)) {
3198 media_desc->set_direction(RtpTransceiverDirection::kSendOnly);
3199 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeRecvOnly)) {
3200 media_desc->set_direction(RtpTransceiverDirection::kRecvOnly);
3201 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeInactive)) {
3202 media_desc->set_direction(RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive);
3203 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeSendRecv)) {
3204 media_desc->set_direction(RtpTransceiverDirection::kSendRecv);
3205 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeExtmapAllowMixed)) {
3206 media_desc->set_extmap_allow_mixed_enum(
3207 MediaContentDescription::kMedia);
3208 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeExtmap)) {
3209 RtpExtension extmap;
3210 if (!ParseExtmap(line, &extmap, error)) {
3211 return false;
3212 }
3213 media_desc->AddRtpHeaderExtension(extmap);
3214 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeXGoogleFlag)) {
3215 // Experimental attribute. Conference mode activates more aggressive
3216 // AEC and NS settings.
3217 // TODO(deadbeef): expose API to set these directly.
3218 std::string flag_value;
3219 if (!GetValue(line, kAttributeXGoogleFlag, &flag_value, error)) {
3220 return false;
3221 }
3222 if (flag_value.compare(kValueConference) == 0)
3223 media_desc->set_conference_mode(true);
3224 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeMsid)) {
3225 if (!ParseMsidAttribute(line, &stream_ids, &track_id, error)) {
3226 return false;
3227 }
3228 *msid_signaling |= cricket::kMsidSignalingMediaSection;
3229 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeRid)) {
3230 const size_t kRidPrefixLength =
3231 kLinePrefixLength + arraysize(kAttributeRid);
3232 if (line.size() <= kRidPrefixLength) {
3233 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Ignoring empty RID attribute: " << line;
3234 continue;
3235 }
3236 RTCErrorOr<RidDescription> error_or_rid_description =
3237 deserializer.DeserializeRidDescription(
3238 line.substr(kRidPrefixLength));
3239
3240 // Malformed a=rid lines are discarded.
3241 if (!error_or_rid_description.ok()) {
3242 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Ignoring malformed RID line: '" << line
3243 << "'. Error: "
3244 << error_or_rid_description.error().message();
3245 continue;
3246 }
3247
3248 rids.push_back(error_or_rid_description.MoveValue());
3249 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeSimulcast)) {
3250 const size_t kSimulcastPrefixLength =
3251 kLinePrefixLength + arraysize(kAttributeSimulcast);
3252 if (line.size() <= kSimulcastPrefixLength) {
3253 return ParseFailed(line, "Simulcast attribute is empty.", error);
3254 }
3255
3256 if (!simulcast.empty()) {
3257 return ParseFailed(line, "Multiple Simulcast attributes specified.",
3258 error);
3259 }
3260
3261 RTCErrorOr<SimulcastDescription> error_or_simulcast =
3262 deserializer.DeserializeSimulcastDescription(
3263 line.substr(kSimulcastPrefixLength));
3264 if (!error_or_simulcast.ok()) {
3265 return ParseFailed(line,
3266 std::string("Malformed simulcast line: ") +
3267 error_or_simulcast.error().message(),
3268 error);
3269 }
3270
3271 simulcast = error_or_simulcast.value();
3272 } else if (HasAttribute(line, kAttributeRtcp)) {
3273 // Ignore and do not log a=rtcp line.
3274 // JSEP section 5.8.2 (media section parsing) says to ignore it.
3275 continue;
3276 } else {
3277 // Unrecognized attribute in RTP protocol.
3278 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "Ignored line: " << line;
3279 continue;
3280 }
3281 } else {
3282 // Only parse lines that we are interested of.
3283 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "Ignored line: " << line;
3284 continue;
3285 }
3286 }
3287
3288 // Remove duplicate or inconsistent rids.
3289 RemoveInvalidRidDescriptions(payload_types, &rids);
3290
3291 // If simulcast is specifed, split the rids into send and receive.
3292 // Rids that do not appear in simulcast attribute will be removed.
3293 // If it is not specified, we assume that all rids are for send layers.
3294 std::vector<RidDescription> send_rids;
3295 std::vector<RidDescription> receive_rids;
3296 if (!simulcast.empty()) {
3297 // Verify that the rids in simulcast match rids in sdp.
3298 RemoveInvalidRidsFromSimulcast(rids, &simulcast);
3299
3300 // Use simulcast description to figure out Send / Receive RIDs.
3301 std::map<std::string, RidDescription> rid_map;
3302 for (const RidDescription& rid : rids) {
3303 rid_map[rid.rid] = rid;
3304 }
3305
3306 for (const auto& layer : simulcast.send_layers().GetAllLayers()) {
3307 auto iter = rid_map.find(layer.rid);
3308 RTC_DCHECK(iter != rid_map.end());
3309 send_rids.push_back(iter->second);
3310 }
3311
3312 for (const auto& layer : simulcast.receive_layers().GetAllLayers()) {
3313 auto iter = rid_map.find(layer.rid);
3314 RTC_DCHECK(iter != rid_map.end());
3315 receive_rids.push_back(iter->second);
3316 }
3317
3318 media_desc->set_simulcast_description(simulcast);
3319 } else {
3320 send_rids = rids;
3321 }
3322
3323 media_desc->set_receive_rids(receive_rids);
3324
3325 // Create tracks from the |ssrc_infos|.
3326 // If the stream_id/track_id for all SSRCS are identical, one StreamParams
3327 // will be created in CreateTracksFromSsrcInfos, containing all the SSRCs from
3328 // the m= section.
3329 if (!ssrc_infos.empty()) {
3330 CreateTracksFromSsrcInfos(ssrc_infos, stream_ids, track_id, &tracks,
3331 *msid_signaling);
3332 } else if (media_type != cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_DATA &&
3333 (*msid_signaling & cricket::kMsidSignalingMediaSection)) {
3334 // If the stream_ids/track_id was signaled but SSRCs were unsignaled we
3335 // still create a track. This isn't done for data media types because
3336 // StreamParams aren't used for SCTP streams, and RTP data channels don't
3337 // support unsignaled SSRCs.
3338 CreateTrackWithNoSsrcs(stream_ids, track_id, send_rids, &tracks);
3339 }
3340
3341 // Add the ssrc group to the track.
3342 for (const SsrcGroup& ssrc_group : ssrc_groups) {
3343 if (ssrc_group.ssrcs.empty()) {
3344 continue;
3345 }
3346 uint32_t ssrc = ssrc_group.ssrcs.front();
3347 for (StreamParams& track : tracks) {
3348 if (track.has_ssrc(ssrc)) {
3349 track.ssrc_groups.push_back(ssrc_group);
3350 }
3351 }
3352 }
3353
3354 // Add the new tracks to the |media_desc|.
3355 for (StreamParams& track : tracks) {
3356 media_desc->AddStream(track);
3357 }
3358
3359 if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
3360 AudioContentDescription* audio_desc = media_desc->as_audio();
3361 UpdateFromWildcardCodecs(audio_desc);
3362
3363 // Verify audio codec ensures that no audio codec has been populated with
3364 // only fmtp.
3365 if (!VerifyAudioCodecs(audio_desc)) {
3366 return ParseFailed("Failed to parse audio codecs correctly.", error);
3367 }
3368 AddAudioAttribute(kCodecParamMaxPTime, maxptime_as_string, audio_desc);
3369 AddAudioAttribute(kCodecParamPTime, ptime_as_string, audio_desc);
3370 }
3371
3372 if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
3373 VideoContentDescription* video_desc = media_desc->as_video();
3374 UpdateFromWildcardCodecs(video_desc);
3375 // Verify video codec ensures that no video codec has been populated with
3376 // only rtcp-fb.
3377 if (!VerifyVideoCodecs(video_desc)) {
3378 return ParseFailed("Failed to parse video codecs correctly.", error);
3379 }
3380 }
3381
3382 // RFC 5245
3383 // Update the candidates with the media level "ice-pwd" and "ice-ufrag".
3384 for (Candidate& candidate : candidates_orig) {
3385 RTC_DCHECK(candidate.username().empty() ||
3386 candidate.username() == transport->ice_ufrag);
3387 candidate.set_username(transport->ice_ufrag);
3388 RTC_DCHECK(candidate.password().empty());
3389 candidate.set_password(transport->ice_pwd);
3390 candidates->push_back(
3391 std::make_unique<JsepIceCandidate>(mline_id, mline_index, candidate));
3392 }
3393
3394 return true;
3395}
3396
3397bool ParseSsrcAttribute(const std::string& line,
3398 SsrcInfoVec* ssrc_infos,
3399 int* msid_signaling,
3400 SdpParseError* error) {
3401 RTC_DCHECK(ssrc_infos != NULL);
3402 // RFC 5576
3403 // a=ssrc:<ssrc-id> <attribute>
3404 // a=ssrc:<ssrc-id> <attribute>:<value>
3405 std::string field1, field2;
3406 if (!rtc::tokenize_first(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength),
3407 kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &field1, &field2)) {
3408 const size_t expected_fields = 2;
3409 return ParseFailedExpectFieldNum(line, expected_fields, error);
3410 }
3411
3412 // ssrc:<ssrc-id>
3413 std::string ssrc_id_s;
3414 if (!GetValue(field1, kAttributeSsrc, &ssrc_id_s, error)) {
3415 return false;
3416 }
3417 uint32_t ssrc_id = 0;
3418 if (!GetValueFromString(line, ssrc_id_s, &ssrc_id, error)) {
3419 return false;
3420 }
3421
3422 std::string attribute;
3423 std::string value;
3424 if (!rtc::tokenize_first(field2, kSdpDelimiterColonChar, &attribute,
3425 &value)) {
3426 rtc::StringBuilder description;
3427 description << "Failed to get the ssrc attribute value from " << field2
3428 << ". Expected format <attribute>:<value>.";
3429 return ParseFailed(line, description.str(), error);
3430 }
3431
3432 // Check if there's already an item for this |ssrc_id|. Create a new one if
3433 // there isn't.
3434 auto ssrc_info_it =
3435 absl::c_find_if(*ssrc_infos, [ssrc_id](const SsrcInfo& ssrc_info) {
3436 return ssrc_info.ssrc_id == ssrc_id;
3437 });
3438 if (ssrc_info_it == ssrc_infos->end()) {
3439 SsrcInfo info;
3440 info.ssrc_id = ssrc_id;
3441 ssrc_infos->push_back(info);
3442 ssrc_info_it = ssrc_infos->end() - 1;
3443 }
3444 SsrcInfo& ssrc_info = *ssrc_info_it;
3445
3446 // Store the info to the |ssrc_info|.
3447 if (attribute == kSsrcAttributeCname) {
3448 // RFC 5576
3449 // cname:<value>
3450 ssrc_info.cname = value;
3451 } else if (attribute == kSsrcAttributeMsid) {
3452 // draft-alvestrand-mmusic-msid-00
3453 // msid:identifier [appdata]
3454 std::vector<std::string> fields;
3455 rtc::split(value, kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &fields);
3456 if (fields.size() < 1 || fields.size() > 2) {
3457 return ParseFailed(
3458 line, "Expected format \"msid:<identifier>[ <appdata>]\".", error);
3459 }
3460 ssrc_info.stream_id = fields[0];
3461 if (fields.size() == 2) {
3462 ssrc_info.track_id = fields[1];
3463 }
3464 *msid_signaling |= cricket::kMsidSignalingSsrcAttribute;
3465 } else if (attribute == kSsrcAttributeMslabel) {
3466 // draft-alvestrand-rtcweb-mid-01
3467 // mslabel:<value>
3468 ssrc_info.mslabel = value;
3469 } else if (attribute == kSSrcAttributeLabel) {
3470 // The label isn't defined.
3471 // label:<value>
3472 ssrc_info.label = value;
3473 }
3474 return true;
3475}
3476
3477bool ParseSsrcGroupAttribute(const std::string& line,
3478 SsrcGroupVec* ssrc_groups,
3479 SdpParseError* error) {
3480 RTC_DCHECK(ssrc_groups != NULL);
3481 // RFC 5576
3482 // a=ssrc-group:<semantics> <ssrc-id> ...
3483 std::vector<std::string> fields;
3484 rtc::split(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength), kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &fields);
3485 const size_t expected_min_fields = 2;
3486 if (fields.size() < expected_min_fields) {
3487 return ParseFailedExpectMinFieldNum(line, expected_min_fields, error);
3488 }
3489 std::string semantics;
3490 if (!GetValue(fields[0], kAttributeSsrcGroup, &semantics, error)) {
3491 return false;
3492 }
3493 std::vector<uint32_t> ssrcs;
3494 for (size_t i = 1; i < fields.size(); ++i) {
3495 uint32_t ssrc = 0;
3496 if (!GetValueFromString(line, fields[i], &ssrc, error)) {
3497 return false;
3498 }
3499 ssrcs.push_back(ssrc);
3500 }
3501 ssrc_groups->push_back(SsrcGroup(semantics, ssrcs));
3502 return true;
3503}

3505bool ParseCryptoAttribute(const std::string& line,
3506 MediaContentDescription* media_desc,
3507 SdpParseError* error) {
3508 std::vector<std::string> fields;
3509 rtc::split(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength), kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &fields);
3510 // RFC 4568
3511 // a=crypto:<tag> <crypto-suite> <key-params> [<session-params>]
3512 const size_t expected_min_fields = 3;
3513 if (fields.size() < expected_min_fields) {
3514 return ParseFailedExpectMinFieldNum(line, expected_min_fields, error);
3515 }
3516 std::string tag_value;
3517 if (!GetValue(fields[0], kAttributeCrypto, &tag_value, error)) {
3518 return false;
3519 }
3520 int tag = 0;
3521 if (!GetValueFromString(line, tag_value, &tag, error)) {
3522 return false;
3523 }
3524 const std::string& crypto_suite = fields[1];
3525 const std::string& key_params = fields[2];
3526 std::string session_params;
3527 if (fields.size() > 3) {
3528 session_params = fields[3];
3529 }
3530 media_desc->AddCrypto(
3531 CryptoParams(tag, crypto_suite, key_params, session_params));
3532 return true;
3533}

3535// Updates or creates a new codec entry in the audio description with according
3536// to |name|, |clockrate|, |bitrate|, and |channels|.
3537void UpdateCodec(int payload_type,
3538 const std::string& name,
3539 int clockrate,
3540 int bitrate,
3541 size_t channels,
3542 AudioContentDescription* audio_desc) {
3543 // Codec may already be populated with (only) optional parameters
3544 // (from an fmtp).
3545 cricket::AudioCodec codec =
3546 GetCodecWithPayloadType(audio_desc->codecs(), payload_type);
3547 codec.name = name;
3548 codec.clockrate = clockrate;
3549 codec.bitrate = bitrate;
3550 codec.channels = channels;
3551 AddOrReplaceCodec<AudioContentDescription, cricket::AudioCodec>(audio_desc,
3552 codec);
3553}

3555// Updates or creates a new codec entry in the video description according to
3556// |name|, |width|, |height|, and |framerate|.
3557void UpdateCodec(int payload_type,
3558 const std::string& name,
3559 VideoContentDescription* video_desc) {
3560 // Codec may already be populated with (only) optional parameters
3561 // (from an fmtp).
3562 cricket::VideoCodec codec =
3563 GetCodecWithPayloadType(video_desc->codecs(), payload_type);
3564 codec.name = name;
3565 AddOrReplaceCodec<VideoContentDescription, cricket::VideoCodec>(video_desc,
3566 codec);

3568
3569bool ParseRtpmapAttribute(const std::string& line,
3570 const cricket::MediaType media_type,
3571 const std::vector<int>& payload_types,
3572 MediaContentDescription* media_desc,
3573 SdpParseError* error) {
3574 std::vector<std::string> fields;
3575 rtc::split(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength), kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &fields);
3576 // RFC 4566
3577 // a=rtpmap:<payload type> <encoding name>/<clock rate>[/<encodingparameters>]
3578 const size_t expected_min_fields = 2;
3579 if (fields.size() < expected_min_fields) {
3580 return ParseFailedExpectMinFieldNum(line, expected_min_fields, error);
3581 }
3582 std::string payload_type_value;
3583 if (!GetValue(fields[0], kAttributeRtpmap, &payload_type_value, error)) {
3584 return false;
3585 }
3586 int payload_type = 0;
3587 if (!GetPayloadTypeFromString(line, payload_type_value, &payload_type,
3588 error)) {
3589 return false;
3590 }
3591
3592 if (!absl::c_linear_search(payload_types, payload_type)) {
3593 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Ignore rtpmap line that did not appear in the "
3594 "<fmt> of the m-line: "
3595 << line;
3596 return true;
3597 }
3598 const std::string& encoder = fields[1];
3599 std::vector<std::string> codec_params;
3600 rtc::split(encoder, '/', &codec_params);
3601 // <encoding name>/<clock rate>[/<encodingparameters>]
3602 // 2 mandatory fields
3603 if (codec_params.size() < 2 || codec_params.size() > 3) {
3604 return ParseFailed(line,
3605 "Expected format \"<encoding name>/<clock rate>"
3606 "[/<encodingparameters>]\".",
3607 error);
3608 }
3609 const std::string& encoding_name = codec_params[0];
3610 int clock_rate = 0;
3611 if (!GetValueFromString(line, codec_params[1], &clock_rate, error)) {
3612 return false;
3613 }
3614 if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
3615 VideoContentDescription* video_desc = media_desc->as_video();
3616 UpdateCodec(payload_type, encoding_name, video_desc);
3617 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
3618 // RFC 4566
3619 // For audio streams, <encoding parameters> indicates the number
3620 // of audio channels. This parameter is OPTIONAL and may be
3621 // omitted if the number of channels is one, provided that no
3622 // additional parameters are needed.
3623 size_t channels = 1;
3624 if (codec_params.size() == 3) {
3625 if (!GetValueFromString(line, codec_params[2], &channels, error)) {
3626 return false;
3627 }
3628 }
3629 AudioContentDescription* audio_desc = media_desc->as_audio();
3630 UpdateCodec(payload_type, encoding_name, clock_rate, 0, channels,
3631 audio_desc);
3632 }
3633 return true;
3634}
3635
3636bool ParseFmtpParam(const std::string& line,
3637 std::string* parameter,
3638 std::string* value,
3639 SdpParseError* error) {
3640 if (!rtc::tokenize_first(line, kSdpDelimiterEqualChar, parameter, value)) {
3641 // Support for non-key-value lines like RFC 2198 or RFC 4733.
3642 *parameter = "";
3643 *value = line;
3644 return true;
3645 }
3646 // a=fmtp:<payload_type> <param1>=<value1>; <param2>=<value2>; ...
3647 return true;
3648}
3649
3650bool ParseFmtpAttributes(const std::string& line,
3651 const cricket::MediaType media_type,
3652 MediaContentDescription* media_desc,
3653 SdpParseError* error) {
3654 if (media_type != cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO &&
3655 media_type != cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
3656 return true;
3657 }
3658
3659 std::string line_payload;
3660 std::string line_params;
3661
3662 // https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4566#section-6
3663 // a=fmtp:<format> <format specific parameters>
3664 // At least two fields, whereas the second one is any of the optional
3665 // parameters.
3666 if (!rtc::tokenize_first(line.substr(kLinePrefixLength),
3667 kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &line_payload,
3668 &line_params)) {
3669 ParseFailedExpectMinFieldNum(line, 2, error);
3670 return false;
3671 }
3672
3673 // Parse out the payload information.
3674 std::string payload_type_str;
3675 if (!GetValue(line_payload, kAttributeFmtp, &payload_type_str, error)) {
3676 return false;
3677 }
3678
3679 int payload_type = 0;
3680 if (!GetPayloadTypeFromString(line_payload, payload_type_str, &payload_type,
3681 error)) {
3682 return false;
3683 }
3684
3685 // Parse out format specific parameters.
3686 std::vector<std::string> fields;
3687 rtc::split(line_params, kSdpDelimiterSemicolonChar, &fields);
3688
3689 cricket::CodecParameterMap codec_params;
3690 for (auto& iter : fields) {
3691 std::string name;
3692 std::string value;
3693 if (!ParseFmtpParam(rtc::string_trim(iter), &name, &value, error)) {
3694 return false;
3695 }
3696 if (codec_params.find(name) != codec_params.end()) {
3697 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Overwriting duplicate fmtp parameter with key \""
3698 << name << "\".";
3699 }
3700 codec_params[name] = value;
3701 }
3702
3703 if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
3704 UpdateCodec<AudioContentDescription, cricket::AudioCodec>(
3705 media_desc, payload_type, codec_params);
3706 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
3707 UpdateCodec<VideoContentDescription, cricket::VideoCodec>(
3708 media_desc, payload_type, codec_params);
3709 }
3710 return true;
3711}
3712
3713bool ParsePacketizationAttribute(const std::string& line,
3714 const cricket::MediaType media_type,
3715 MediaContentDescription* media_desc,
3716 SdpParseError* error) {
3717 if (media_type != cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
3718 return true;
3719 }
3720 std::vector<std::string> packetization_fields;
3721 rtc::split(line.c_str(), kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &packetization_fields);
3722 if (packetization_fields.size() < 2) {
3723 return ParseFailedGetValue(line, kAttributePacketization, error);
3724 }
3725 std::string payload_type_string;
3726 if (!GetValue(packetization_fields[0], kAttributePacketization,
3727 &payload_type_string, error)) {
3728 return false;
3729 }
3730 int payload_type;
3731 if (!GetPayloadTypeFromString(line, payload_type_string, &payload_type,
3732 error)) {
3733 return false;
3734 }
3735 std::string packetization = packetization_fields[1];
3736 UpdateVideoCodecPacketization(media_desc->as_video(), payload_type,
3737 packetization);
3738 return true;
3739}
3740
3741bool ParseRtcpFbAttribute(const std::string& line,
3742 const cricket::MediaType media_type,
3743 MediaContentDescription* media_desc,
3744 SdpParseError* error) {
3745 if (media_type != cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO &&
3746 media_type != cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
3747 return true;
3748 }
3749 std::vector<std::string> rtcp_fb_fields;
3750 rtc::split(line.c_str(), kSdpDelimiterSpaceChar, &rtcp_fb_fields);
3751 if (rtcp_fb_fields.size() < 2) {
3752 return ParseFailedGetValue(line, kAttributeRtcpFb, error);
3753 }
3754 std::string payload_type_string;
3755 if (!GetValue(rtcp_fb_fields[0], kAttributeRtcpFb, &payload_type_string,
3756 error)) {
3757 return false;
3758 }
3759 int payload_type = kWildcardPayloadType;
3760 if (payload_type_string != "*") {
3761 if (!GetPayloadTypeFromString(line, payload_type_string, &payload_type,
3762 error)) {
3763 return false;
3764 }
3765 }
3766 std::string id = rtcp_fb_fields[1];
3767 std::string param = "";
3768 for (std::vector<std::string>::iterator iter = rtcp_fb_fields.begin() + 2;
3769 iter != rtcp_fb_fields.end(); ++iter) {
3770 param.append(*iter);
3771 }
3772 const cricket::FeedbackParam feedback_param(id, param);
3773
3774 if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
3775 UpdateCodec<AudioContentDescription, cricket::AudioCodec>(
3776 media_desc, payload_type, feedback_param);
3777 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
3778 UpdateCodec<VideoContentDescription, cricket::VideoCodec>(
3779 media_desc, payload_type, feedback_param);
3780 }
3781 return true;
3782}
